SUMMARY: V1 was traveling northbound on a three lane highway. V1 was traveling in the third lane. A non contacted vehicle changed lanes in front of V1. V1 attempted to avoid contact by steering to the right. V1 then lost control and departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted a concrete barrier. V1 then rotated counter clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the concrete barrier. V1 continued to rotate and returned to the roadway. V1 came to rest facing south in the northbound lanes.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  V2 was legally parked facing westbound.  The front of V1 contacted the front of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound in the right lane of a two lane roadway.  An unknown vehicle encroached into V1's lane and  V1 attempted to avoid the unknown vehicle by braking and steering left. V1 departed the left side of the roadway and the frontal plane of V1 struck a guardrail.

V1 was traveling eastbound.  V2 was traveling eastbound, slowing to a stop.  V3 was traveling eastbound, stopped in traffic.  The frontal plane of V1 struck the rear of V2.  This caused the frontal plane of V2 to impact the rear of V3.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane 1 of a two-way, two lane, undivided roadway passing through a 4 way intersection.  V2 was traveling northeast through the same intersection when the front end of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  The force of the initial impact caused both V1 and V2 to depart the roadway at the northeast corner of the intersection.

V1,V2, and V3 were traveling north on a two way, 7 lane, non-divided roadway when V3 stopped to make a left hand turn, V2 was in between V1 and V3. V1 struck the rear of V2 pushing the front of V2 into the rear of V3, V3 then left the scene.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane two of a three lane road approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling northbound in lane two of a two lane road proceeding into the intersection.  As V1 and V2 entered the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.
V1 was traveling southbound in lane 3 of a divided roadway, V2 was traveling in lane 2 of the same roadway.  V1 changed lanes to the right and the front of V2 contacted the back of V1.
V1 was westbound on roadway. V2 was southbound on intersecting roadway. V1 and V2 entered into the same intersection. The front of V2 impacted with the right of V1.
V1 was traveling southbound and departed the right side of the roadway.  The front of V1 contacted a tree.

V1 was traveling west in lane three of a one-way roadway with four lanes of travel.  V2 was traveling in lane 2 of the same roadway.  On this roadway, the right side of V1 contacted the left side plane of V2.
V1 and V2 were both traveling south at a traffic signal controlled intersection. V2 was ahead of V1. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane.
V1 and V2 were both traveling Northwest on a three lane (with center two-way turn lane) non-divided roadway. In their original travel lane, the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.
Vehicle 1 was heading north on a two-way four lane city street. V2 was heading south. V1 turned left and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling on a one lane, one way, exit ramp west bound. V1 departed roadway to the right where the front of V1 came into contact with a guard rail. V2 then rotated counterclockwise and made contact with the guard rail on the right side.
V1 and V2 were both traveling in a North east direction, in lane 2. V2 had come to a stop and V1's front collided with V2's rear.

V1 westbound on two lane roadway. V2 eastbound on same roadway. V1 departed the travel lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted with the left of V2. V1 then returned to original travel lane in a clockwise rotation. V1 departed the roadway to the right and impacted with a utility pole with the left side. V1 came to final rest in against the same utility pole.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection V2 attempted to turn left and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was travelling south on a 3 lane two way traffic roadway with a two way center left turn lane. Vehicle 1 loss control and departed the right side of the road making contact with the curb on the front plane of the vehicle, RF tire, and continuing into a power pole which contacted the front plane.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east.  V1 departed the road to the left and the front of V1 contacted an impact attenuator.

V1 was Northbound on a 7 lane road. V1 was in the left turn lane (lane 4) . V2 was South bound in the #2 lane. V2 continued through the intersection as V1 turned left. The front of V2 struck the right side of V1.  V1 rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 struck the front of V3, which was facing East and was stationary at traffic signal.

Vehicle #1 was traveling North. The road began to curve left, and V1 departed the road to the right. V1 over-corrected to the left, then over-corrected to the right and began to rotate clockwise. V1 departed the road to the right and rolled over two quarter turns. The roll was interrupted by a barbed wire fence.

V1 was traveling southbound through an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound through the same intersection (created by driveway exits and entrances). In this intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the right side of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west bound. A deer was in the roadway. V1 made contact with the deer. The plane of contact was the front bumper.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound and approaching an intersection to turn left. Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound and approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2.
Vehicle one was heading southwest on a two lane street attempting to enter a driveway when the frontal plane impacted bushes on the left side of the driveway entrance.

V1 negotiated a right curve after passing through an intersection and was traveling in the Number 2 lane of of the southbound portion of a 5 lane roadway composed of 3 lanes of southbound traffic and 2 lanes of northbound traffic. V1 lost traction on the wet roadway and spun clockwise approximately 180 degrees while traversing the Number 1 lane of the roadway. V1 struck a raised curb on the right side of the roadway and came to final rest facing south straddling the curb and an adjacent flower bed.

V2 was traveling north on a three lane roadway in lane one, approaching an intersection.  V1 was also traveling north on the same roadway in lane two next to V2.  V2 was attempting to avoid a snow bank and steered left when the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane, two way roadway, attempting to turn left at the intersection.  V2 was heading west on a the same roadway, passing through the intersection.  The front of V2 made contact with the right side of V1.
V1 was traveling southbound toward an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound toward the same intersection. During the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1, passing through the intersection. V2 was traveling south turning left (east) in the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and V2 counterclockwise. Both vehicles impacted again in a side slap impact. V1 continued to move north and departed the roadway at the northeast corner of the intersection. The front impacted a wooden utility pole. V1 rotated counter clockwise and impacted a metal pole with its right side then a traffic sign pole with its right side. V1 kept rotating and impacted the guy wire of a utility pole with its back. After the first two impacts V2 kept rotating counter clockwise and rolled onto its right side. V2 slid off the road and rolled back onto its wheels.

V1 was north bound on a one way non-divided roadway. V1 left the roadway to the right where it impacted a guardrail on the frontal plane. V1 rotated clockwise, and crossed back over the both lanes of travel, where it impacted a cable barrier with it back plane. The vehicle rotated counter clockwise, where it obtained damage to the left plane and the front plane from the cable barrier impact.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of a two-way undivided roadway. Another vehicle headed in the opposite direction on the same roadway was overtaking a vehicle and encroached into V1's lane. V1 departed the right lane and then the right side of the roadway down into a ditch causing the front and right side of the vehicle to contact the ditch.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane undivided roadway when it departed the right side of roadway and struck a mailbox and then a utility pole, both with its right side, before coming to a final rest.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, with no lane lines, and lost control on the snow-covered roadway. V1 departed the road to the right into a corn field in a clockwise yaw, then tripped and rolled over to the left four quarter-turns.

V1 was traveling northbound and V2 was traveling eastbound on a crossing street. V3 was parked legally facing westbound. The front left corner of V1 impacted the front right corner of V2. Both vehicles rotated and the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 continued forward and the front end of V1 impacted the front end of V3.

Vehicle was traveling southbound approaching an intersection controlled with a stop light. V1 began braking and begun to slid through the intersection in a slight clockwise yaw before exiting the roadway to the southeast corner where the front of V1 struck a power box.
Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two-lane roadway when it departed the left (east) side of the road and its right side impacted a fence.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on an off-ramp from a major highway, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 lost control on the wet surface, entered a counter-clockwise yaw and departed the lane to the left, and then the road to the left, and impacted a guardrail with the front plane. V1 bounced off of the guardrail, re-entered and crossed the roadway, and then departed the road to the right, still in a counter-clockwise yaw, and came to rest in a grass ditch.
V1 was northbound on the 4 lane roadway. V2 was westbound on 4 lane one way roadway. The front of V2 impacted with the right rear of V1.
V1 and V2 were both traveling southbound on roadway. The front of V2 collided with the back of V1.
V1 and V2 traveling north on highway. V2 ahead of V1. V1's frontal plane contacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound on an undivided two-lane roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on the crossing undivided three-lane roadway attempting to pass through the same intersection. V2’s front plane struck the left plane of V1. V1 began to rotate in a counterclockwise rotation, departing the roadway to the north, its right rear tire striking the curb before striking a tree with its rear plane and coming to final rest.
V2 was stopped at a four way stop. V1 traveling south on roadway in the same direction as V2 approaching from rear. V1's frontal plane contacted V2's rear plane.

V1 was traveling northbound on an undivided 5 lane roadway in lane three, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue into a parking lot. V2 was traveling southbound on the same roadway in lane one. V3 was facing east, stopped at the light at the exit of the parking lot. The front of V2 struck the right side of V1, causing V1 to begin to rotate clockwise. V1 rotated into the exit lanes of the parking lot, its left top striking a utility pole and then striking V3 on the left side.
Vehicles 1, 2, and 3 were headed west on a three lane divided city street at an intersection controlled by signals. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. The front of V2 impacted the back of V3.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south. V1 traveled across the northbound lane and departed the left side of the roadway onto a dirt shoulder. V1 began rotating in a clockwise direction.V1 rolled left four 1/4 turns before coming to rest in its wheels facing west with its front wheels on the roadway and the rear wheels off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the right side of the roadway with its right wheels. V1 returned to the roadway. V1 traveled off the right side of the roadway again. The front of V1 impacted a wooden utility pole. V1 rolled 1/4 turn to the left where it came to rest on it its left side facing southwest.
V1 was traveling northbound when a deer ran into the roadway. The front of V1 struck the deer and departed the east side of the roadway.
Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound in the second of three lanes approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was stopped eastbound in the same lane ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling east approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north through the same intersection. The frontal plane of V1 struck the left side of V2.  V2 rotated counterclockwise and struck a utility pole on the right rear.

V1 was traveling southbound. V2 was traveling eastbound. In the intersection, the front end of V2 came in contact with the right side of V1. V1 then departed the road on the left, contacting a curb and a traffic signal pole.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in the left turn lane on a 6-lane roadway turning south at the intersection.  Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 6-lane roadway crossing through the same intersection when the front of Vehicle 2 contacted the right side of Vehicle 1.

Vehicle #1 was parked in a private drive with its trailer still partly in the roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling south bound on the intersecting roadway and its front end impacted the right side of the trailer.
V1 was heading southbound when V1 lost control departing the roadway and striking a pole with the front of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane roadway approaching the same intersection.  V3 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  The right side of V2 then contacted the left side of V1.  The right side of V2 then contacted the front of V3.  Then the front of V1 contacted the ground off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-way two-lane roadway negotiating a curve right. V1 departed the left side of the road and its left side impacted a curb. V1 continued to travel west and its front impacted a second curb.

V1 was traveling west, V2 traveling east on an undivided two-lane curved roadway. V1 failed to negotiate a left hand curve, departing the roadway to the right. As V1 returned to the roadway, it crossed over the centerline, its front end striking the front end of V2. V1 overturned one-quarter turn to the right, striking the left rear side of V1 as it landed on its right right as it came to final rest. V2 came to final rest facing south, partly off the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound in the left turning lane of a two way undivided roadway with two lanes of travel and a two way left turn lane. V2 was traveling eastbound in the right lane on the same roadway. As V1 was making a left turn, the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the right plane of V1.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction.  V2 was traveling southbound also on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction.  At the intersection of the above roadways, the frontal plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction attempting to turn south.  V2 was traveling southbound also on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction.  At the intersection of the above roadways, the frontal plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2.

V1 was traveling south, approaching a four-way intersection, on a four-lane roadway having two lanes of northbound traffic and two lanes of southbound traffic. At the traffic signal controlled intersection the southbound portion of the roadway includes a dedicated left turn lane and a dedicated right turn lane. Just prior to entering the intersection V1 was traveling in the number three lane. V2 and V3 were stopped at a red light waiting to proceed north throught the intersection. At the traffic signal controlled intersection the northbound portion of the roadway includes a dedicated left turn lane. As V1 moved into the intersection it turned to the left, traveled across the intersection, and the front of V1 collided with the front of V2 which was stopped in the number two northbound lane. After colliding with V2 the front of V1 also collided with the front of V3 which was stopped in the number one northbound lane.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, one way roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and rolled over four quarter turns and struck a fence.
V1 was north bound on a a two lane non-divided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left. V1 impacted the deer with its frontal plane.

V2 was traveling south on a two-lane roadway and departed the right (west) side of the roadway, impacting the rear plane of V1 (parked vehicle) with its right side plane (Event 1). V1 was redirected back onto the roadway and subsequently departed the west roadside again,  impacting two chain-link fences with its frontal plane (Events 2 & 3).

V1 was traveling west bound in lane 1 of 2. Ice on the road caused V1 to depart the roadway where the front of V1 came into contact with a guide wire of a power pole. This caused V1 to roll left 3 quarter turns came to a stop on the passenger side of the vehicle.

V1 was northbound on roadway approaching the intersection. V2 as southbound on same roadway approaching the intersection. V3 was eastbound on intersecting roadway and stopped at the traffic light. V1 made a left turn at the intersection and V2 made a right turn at the intersection. V2 slowed due to traffic. The front of V1 collided with the back of V2. The front of V2 then collided with the left side of V3.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound on the highway in an interchange area. V1 changed lanes to the left and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2.  V2 rotated clockwise and the left and back of V2 contacted a guardrail.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling westbound on a two lane one direction roadway.  Due to another vehicles actions V3 slowed in traffic, as a result V2 was also forced to slow down.  The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2 which caused the front of V2 to be pushed forward into V3.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane roadway entering an intersection.  V2 was traveling east on a two lane, two way roadway, through the same intersection.  The front of V1 made contact with the left side of V2.  V2 continued traveling south west, exiting the roadway with the front of V2 making contact with a utility pole.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-way, four lane, roadway, in lane two.   V2 was on the same roadway, making a left turn, heading southbound.  The front of V1 made contact with the right side of V2,  V2 rotated clockwise, coming to rest on the south east corner of the intersection, facing west.

V1 was headed north on the 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 was negotiating the beginning of a curve to the right when it lost control on the wet road, departed the roadway on the left side, and slid into a grouping of small trees and into a ditch; both impacting its left side.

Vehicle 1 was headed north in lane 2 of a divided roadway.  Vehicle 1 began to merge into lane 1 where it lost control on the slush covered road, departed lane 1 into lane 2, made 2 full counterclockwise rotations while departing lane 2 to the left onto the shoulder.  Vehicle 1 then contacted the dividing concrete barrier with its front end, continued 1 additional half rotation counterclockwise, and then struck the barrier again with its rear and came to final rest on the shoulder.
V1 was traveling North in lane two of a three lane, wet, divided highway when it departed the roadway to the left side. The front of V1 contacted a cable barrier on the left side of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling east bound on the same two lane non-divided roadway. V2 slowed for another vehicle. When V2 slowed, V1's frontal plane impacted V2's rear plane. V1 then impacted a snow/ice bank on north side of the road with its frontal plane.
Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling northbound in lane two on a roadway approaching a four way intersection. V2, which was ahead of V1, stopped and V1 rear ended V2.

V1 was eastbound on a 4 lane roadway. V2 was westbound on the same roadway. V1 steered left in avoidance of a stopped vehicle and departed the travel lane to the left. The front left of V1 impacted with the left front of V2. V2 then rotated counter clockwise and the right side impacted with an utility pole where it came to final rest.
V1 was headed northbound on a wet and snow covered four lane roadway . V1 rotated clockwise, departed the roadway to the right and contacted a concrete wall with the front.
V1 was eastbound, approaching an intersection, making a right hand turn to continue south. V1 ran off the roadway to the left striking the curb with the undercarriage.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west and sustained a loss of control on the snow-covered roadway. V1 departed it's lane of travel to the right, then departed the road to the right and impacted a guardrail face with the front plane.

V1 was traveling south on an entry ramp to a major highway. V2 was traveling on the same entrance ramp, ahead of V1. After entering the southbound lanes of the highway,  V2 came to a complete stop due to backed up traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.
V1 was traveling south on a highway. The driver of V1 fell to sleep and lost control of the vehicle. V1 departed the roadway to the right and started to roll over for 6 quarter turns.

V1 was traveling east approaching V2 and V3 that were stopped in the travel lane at a red light. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.  V2 was displaced forward and the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3.
V1 was traveling northbound through the intersection. V2 was traveling westbound through the intersection. V1 and V2 crossed paths and the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was driving southbound in the second lane on a five lane roadway. V1 crossed over the lane line on the left and exited the roadway where it impacted a curb, continued south and contacted a fence, where the vehicle came to final rest.
V1 was traveling eastbound in lane 2 of a physically divided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail end.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two-way, two lane, roadway.  V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 made contact with a tree.
Vehicle #1 was stopped facing east bound. Vehicle #2 was traveling south bound. Both vehicles entered the intersection and V2 impacted the front bumper on the back left side of V1.
V1 was traveling in a south easterly direction when it's left side impacted with a deer crossing the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right  and drove over the side walk continuing forward then striking a tree with the front plane.  The impact caused V1 to  counter clockwise to its final rest.
V1 was traveling southbound in lane two of a two-lane highway. V1 departed the left side of the roadway, completing six quarter-turns before coming to rest on its roof, in the center median.
V1 and V2 were westbound on an undivided roadway. V2 was stopped at the intersection. The front of V1 struck the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane two-way roadway, when it hit a snow wind drift with ice. V1 exited the roadway to right, and struck a guardrail end. V1 contacted the guardrail two other times on the left side. V1 came to final rest with guardrail still contacting the left side of vehicle.
V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 traveling north on highway. V2 traveling north on highway in front of V1. V3 traveling north on highway behind V1. V1 contacted its frontal plane with V2's rear plane. Approaching from rear V3 contacted its frontal plane with V1s rear plane.
V1 and V2 were travelling on a three lane two way road. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2 at an intersection.

V1 was Westbound on a three lane  two way highway. V2 was Eestbound on the same road in the inside lane. There were two lane of Eastbound traffic and one lane for Westbound traffic. V1 encountered some black ice. The front of V1 struck the front of V2. V1 then struck the Eastbound Guardrail .

V1 and V2 were both eastbound in the same lane of a divided highway. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 exited the right (south) side of the roadway where its front impacted a concrete barrier. V1 also departed the right (south) side of the roadway where its front then right side impacted a concrete barrier where it continued forward and an unknown plane contacted a traffic sign post.

Vehicle 1 was negotiating a left curve northbound in the first of three lanes. Vehicle 2 was negotiating a left curve northbound in the second lane ahead of V1. A non-contact vehicle was stopped partially in lane one. The driver of V1 steered left to avoid the non-contact vehicle and then right attempting to avoid V2. V2 had slowed due to traffic and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. The driver of V1 lost directional control of the vehicle. V1 departed the roadway on the left side. The left side of V1 struck the concrete traffic barrier, briefly returned to the roadway before again departing the roadway and contacting the concrete traffic barrier with the front of V1 .
V1 and V2 were both westbound in the same lane of a three-lane divided highway. V1 was stopped ahead of V2. The front of V2 impacted the back of V1.
Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast.  V1 lost control and began rotating.  V1 departed the road to the left.  The right of V1 contacted the snow/ground.
V1 turned south at a four-way intersection onto a two-lane roadway.  V2 was parked facing south on the right curb of the roadway.  While turning the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound through the intersection.  V2 was traveling from eastbound to northbound through the intersection.  In the intersection, the front end of V1 came into contact with the right side of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south. Vehicle #2 was traveling north. V1 departed its lane to the left and the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.

V1 was eastbound toward an intersection. V2 was northbound toward the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 (event 1). Subsequently, the left side of V1 slapped the left side of V2 (event 2). V2 departed the northeast corner of the intersection where its right side struck a pole (event 3). V1 departed the same northeast intersection where its front end impacted a pole (event 4).

Vehicle 1 was traveling north. Vehicle 2 was traveling south. V1 initiated a left hand turn and the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. The front plane of V2 then contacted a sign post and a sprinkler system.

V1 was traveling southbound on an exit ramp with one lane of travel. V2 was traveling westbound in the first lane on a two way roadway with four lanes of travel in each direction. As V1 was merging and changing lanes onto the roadway, the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the right plane of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound in the right lane of a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction attempting to back up to enter a driveway.  V2 was traveling southbound in the left lane of the same roadway attempting to turn left into the driveway heading eastbound.  On this roadway, the frontal plane of V2 contacted the rear plane of V1.

Vehicle one was traveling east in lane 2 on a 2-lane one-way exit ramp when it departed the left road edge and contacted an impact attenuator with its front. Vehicle 1 then rotated counter-clockwise and contacted a concrete barrier with its rear.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north.  Vehicle #2 was traveling east on an intersecting roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right of V2.
Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound through the intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound through the intersection. V1 contacted V2 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling westbound in the wrong direction on a one way street. V2 was traveling north on a two lane street toward the intersection. During the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.
V1 was Eastbound on a two way, two lane road approaching an intersection. V2 was Northbound on a three lane, one way street in the outside lane. The right side of  V1 contacted the Left side of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south bound. V1 departed the roadway on the left side and impacted the front bumper on a guard rail. V1 entered the roadway from the left side and impacted the bridge located on the right side of the roadway with the back bumper.

V1 was traveling southbound through an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound through the same intersection. In the intersection, the front end of V1 came in contact with the left side of V2. The right side of V1 then contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling North on a divided two lane freeway in wet weather. V1 was traveling in lane one when they approached a slower moving vehicle. V1 moved into lane two. The slower moving vehicle also moved into the number two lane. At this moment, a large amount of water hit the windshield of V1 and V1 lost control and departed the road to the right. The front of V1 struck a steep embankment before the vehicle spun and the rear of V1 struck a tree.

V1,V2,V3 and V4 were all traveling south west in the same lane. V2, V3 and V4 stopped for traffic. The front of V1 struck the back of V2. V2's front then contacted the back of V3. V3's front then contacted the back of V4.

V1 was traveling northbound on  a two-lane, two way, roadway.  V2 was traveling behind V1 heading northbound on the same roadway.  V2 stopped in the roadway to make a left turn and the front of V1 made contact with the rear of V2.

V1 was approaching a Y-shaped intersection intending to turn left.  The roadway conditions were icy causing V1 to loose control and depart the roadway on the right side where the front plane struck two trees.

V1 was traveling northbound approaching an intersection controlled by a stop sign.  V2 was towing a trailer, traveling eastbound passing through the intersection.  The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2's the trailer.

V1 and V2 were traveling north in lane 2 of a 3-lane divided roadway with left turn lane approaching a 4 way intersection.  V1 decelerated for slowing traffic.  The front end of V2 contacted the rear end of V1.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in Lane 1 of a divided roadway, approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane 3 of the same divided roadway, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue west at the same intersection. Vehicle 1’s front plane struck the right plane of Vehicle 2. After the initial impact, Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and struck a sign with its left side before coming to final rest. Vehicle 2 also departed the roadway to its left, also striking a sign with its front before coming to final rest.
V1 and V2 were both traveling North in lane 1 of a 2-way undivided roadway.  The front end of V1 contacted the rear end of V2.

V1 was traveling north bound on a main roadway and V2 was traveling south bound on the same roadway. V1 moved to the left turn lane to turn east onto a secondary street (at the light). Both V1 and V2 had the green light. V1 turned in front of V2 as it was entering the intersection. V1 front end made contact with V2 front end.  Both vehicles had to be towed from the scene due to damages.  V1 driver was taken to a medical facility by ambulance.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one of a four-lane, physically divided roadway when it departed the right side of the road and impacted a concrete barrier (Event 1) with its right side.  The vehicle traversed all southbound travel lanes to the left and impacted the center median concrete barrier with its left fender (Event 2) and again with its left quarter-panel (Event 3)) before coming to rest.

V1 was eastbound on roadway entering a four legged, light controlled intersection. V2 was westbound on the same roadway entering the same intersection. V1 made a left turn at the intersection. V2 continued straight at the intersection. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling on a three lane road toward a junction. As V1 approached the intersecting junction it continued straight. The front of V1 contacted a concrete barrier. The front of V1 then caught on fire.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane roadway negotiating a left-hand turn. V1 lost control and departed the roadway on the left hand side where the front plane struck a tree.

V1 was traveling south, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling east in the Number 2 eastbound lane of a six-lane roadway composed of two lanes of eastbound traffic, two lanes of westbound traffic, and two eastbound dedicated left turn lanes. V1 departed the left side of the roadway. The front of V1 struck a reflective roadside warning sign. V1 continued traveling in the median and the front left of V1 struck a tree.
V1 traveling eastbound entering intersection. V2 traveling Southbound entering same intersection. Frontal plane of V2 struck left side of V1

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided road. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided road. V1's frontal plane struck V2's right side plane in a four way intersection. V1's left side plane then struck V2's right side plane (side slap) causing V1 to spin in a counterclockwise rotation. V1 came to final rest off the road, on the south west corner of the intersection, headed east. V2 went off the road on the south west corner of the road striking an embankment with its front plane. V2 then spun clockwise 90 degrees striking the embankment with its left side plane. V2 came to final rest with its left side against the embankment heading north east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east, attempting to make a left turn and entered into the intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south approaching the intersection in the #4 travel lane. While doing so, the front plane of Vehicle 2 impacted the mid, left side of  Vehicle 1 causing Vehicle 1 to rotate counter clockwise. While rotating counter clockwise, Vehicle 2's left frontal side plane made a secondary contact with Vehicle 1's left rear side plane. After disengagement with Vehicle 2, Vehicle 1 continued rotating counter clockwise where the right rear plane then struck a sign post before coming to final rest.

Vehicle 2 was going north on a four lane undivided roadway traveling thru an intersection. Vehicle 1 was going west on an undivided four lane roadway, crossing the intersection. Within the intersection Vehicle 1's frontal plane impacted Vehicle 2's right plane.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four-lane trafficway divided by a concrete barrier. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where it struck a curb and continued across the sidewalk where the front plane stuck a concrete wall.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane road approaching a four-way intersection controlled by a stop sign.  V2 was traveling northbound approaching the intersection. V1 started from the stop sign attempting to cross through the intersection and the right plane was struck by the front plane of V2. After initial impact V1 departed the road on the northeast corner where the front plane struck a light post. V2 also departed the road on the northeast corner and the front plane struck a building.
V1 was traveling easterly in lane 1 of an undivided, four-lane roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway as its frontal plane impacted a utility pole (Event 1) and then a mailbox (Event 2).

V1 was traveling north with a towed trailer in lane 1 of a 2 way undivided roadway.  V2 was also traveling with a motorcycle on a trailer in the same lane behind V1.  V1 slowed to make a left turn and the front end of V2 contacted the rear end of the trailer of V1.  The force of the impact caused the motorcycle to come loose from the trailer of V2 and struck the rear end of V2.

V1 and V2 were both headed north in lane 1 of a 2 lane, undivided roadway, and were approaching a 3 way intersection.  V1 stopped to make a left turn at the intersection and V2 made contact with its front end to V1's back end.

V1 was traveling west in lane 1 of a 2 way undivided roadway approaching a T-intersection.  V1 made an end departure from the roadway and contacted a small tree stump with the front end of V1 before overturning one quarter turn and coming to a final rest on its right side.

Vehicle 1 was traveling North on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, V1 departed it's travel lane to the left, V1 then ran off the left side of the road. V1 continued down an embankment, V1 front contacted a tree.

V1 was traveling the wrong direction on a two lane roadway in lane one. When approaching an exit ramp from a major highway, V1 veered to the left and departed the roadway. V1 then began to rotate counter clockwise, and rolled over right side leading four quarter turns.

V1 was stopped at an intersection, waiting to complete a left turn. V2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. V3 was traveling north, passing through the intersection. Within the intersection,  the front of V2 impacted the right side of V3. V3 started to rotate clockwise. The left side of V3 impacted the front of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east, approaching a T-intersection and then entered the intersection turning left. Before completing the turn, V1 departed the intersecting road to the right and impacted a curb with the front tires and then contacted a wood utility pole with the front plane.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane roadway in lane one where passing is allowed and attempted to pass other vehicles in the opposing lane. As V1 returned to the right (driving lane) the vehicle went over the rumble strips. V1 over-corrected the vehicle back to the left and then over-corrected to the right and lost control. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 struck a delineator post. Once again V1 over-corrected to the left causing the vehicle to rotate counter-clockwise across the road and then depart the left side of the roadway.  V1 rolled right side leading and during the roll contacted a barb-wire fence and V1 overturned 3 times.

Vehicles 1, 2 & 3 (in that sequence) were traveling west on an undivided two way, two lane highway. Vehicle 1 slowed down and stopped with the traffic flow.  Vehicle 2 and Vehicle 3 braked and moved to the right shoulder to avoid colliding with Vehicle 1.  The front of Vehicle 3 collided into the rear of Vehicle 2, causing the front left corner of Vehicle 2 to collide into the right rear corner of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 2 veered to the right, departed the highway and came to the rest on the right shoulder. Vehicle 2 was towed from the scene.
V1 was traveling southbound following roadway when V2, traveling eastbound  through intersection impacted V1 with frontal plan on V1's Left plane
V1 was traveling east towards an intersection.  V2 was traveling south towards the same intersection.  In the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.
V1 was traveling north, turning left onto intersecting street. V2 was traveling south and contacted the front of V1 with left side plane

V1 was northbound on a four lane undivided roadway. V2 was southbound on same roadway. V1 begun process of left turn onto westbound roadway. V2 entered the same intersection continuing to proceed in southbound direction. The front of V2 impacted with the right front side of V1. V1 came to a controlled final rest facing westbound. V2 came to a controlled final rest facing southbound.
V1 and V2 were traveling north in the far right lane on a three lane one way highway. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the original lane.

V1 and V2 were northbound in the first lane on a 4 lane divided interstate. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2. V2 departed the roadway to the right and came to an uncontrolled final rest approximately 100 yards from the shoulder. V2 traveled a few feet forward of point of impact to come to an uncontrolled final rest.

V1 was traveling east on a non-divided two way roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. V2 veered south into the lane V1 was traveling in and the left front of V1 contacted the left front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the south side of the roadway headed south.

V1 and V2 were traveling west in lane two of a two lane one way roadway. V1 slowed down. V2 attempted to avoid V1 by steering right and struck the rear plane of V1 with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the north shoulder. V2 came to final rest partially on the north shoulder and partially on lane one.
V1 was driving northbound on a two-lane divided roadway. V1 lost control and departed the roadway to the left, into the median. The frontal plane of V1 struck the face of a guardrail.

V1 was traveling Northbound on a two lane roadway.  V2 and V3 were parked legally facing northbound on the east side of the road.  The frontal plane of V1 struck the rear of V2, which caused V2's frontal plane to impact the rear of V3.
V2 was traveling westbound and stopped at a traffic signal, V1 was traveling westbound along the same lane of travel when the front plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.
V1 was traveling north in lane 2 of a four lane, undivided roadway and V2 was traveling south in lane 2. V1 departed it's lane to the left and the front of V1 struck the front of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound on a 2-lane undivided roadway.  V1 departed the road to the right and the front of V1 contacted a 20cm diameter tree, then the right of V1 contacted a 20cm diameter tree.  V1s back end came off the ground and a 40cm tree branch contacted the top of V1.  The front of V1 then contacted a 15cm diameter tree and then a 1m diameter bolder.  V1 then rotated clockwise and tripped over 4 quarter turns to the left.  V1s driver was completely ejected out right front window.
V1 was attempting to pull out of a private drive/roadway, turning left to travel east bound. V2 was was west bound on the intersecting roadway. V2's frontal plane impacted V1's left plane.

V1 and V2 were traveling on the same two lane non divided roadway. V1 was south bound when it attempted to make a left turn across the north bound traffic lane. V2 was north bound. V1's frontal plane impacted V2's frontal plane. V2 then impacted a road sign with its frontal plane, before coming to final rest.

V1, V2, V3 and V4 were traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane roadway. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2. The frontal plane of V2 then impacted the rear plane of V3. The frontal plane of V3 then impacted the rear plane of V4.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane one of a two lane roadway. V2 was traveling northbound in lane one of a two lane roadway. The frontal plane of V2 impacted the left side plane of V1. V1 rotated, impacted a curb and then a wall, where it came to final rest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south bound in lane two, of a two lane, divided interstate roadway, V1 departed the roadway on the left and impacted the front plane on the guardrail end.  V1 then rolled 4 quarter turns, left side leading.

V1 was southbound on roadway preparing to turn left across northbound traffic. V2 was northbound preparing to turn right into a parking lot. V1 turned left across northbound lanes at the same time V2 began to turn left into the parking lot. The front of V2 collided with the right front of V1. V1 came to a controlled final rest in the parking lot entry way. V2 came to final rest at point of impact.
V1 and V2 were traveling north on two lane, two way road. V2 slowed down intending to make a left turn into a parking lot. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling south on a curved left, four lane, two way road. V1 departed the right side of the road and impacted a sign post, and a tree with the front plane.

V1 was eastbound stopped at an intersection attempting to turn north. V2 was southbound on a two lane physically divided roadway. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 causing damage. V1 was spun counterclockwise coming to rest in the intersection. V2 was spun counter clockwise coming to final rest in intersection.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane undivided unmarked road. Due to weather a utility pole had fallen across the roadway. V1 impacted the utility pole with the front plane, and then with the undercarriage.

V1 and V2 were westbound on a two lane roadway. A non-contact vehicle pulled from the North shoulder of the roadway and proceeded in front of V2. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 came to final rest on the north shoulder facing west just before the exit ramp. V1 came to final rest on the north edge of the roadway facing west just past the exit ramp.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east and Vehicle #2 was traveling north; both vehicles were approaching the same intersection. The vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling southwest approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest approaching the same intersection. V1's left plane was contacted by V2's front plane.
Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were traveling north on a two-lane undivided roadway; V2 was ahead of V1 stopped in traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound in the second of three lanes. Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound in the third of three lanes. V1 departed the original travel lane on the left side. The left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. The driver of V1 lost directional control of the vehicle and departed the roadway on the left side. The front of V1 contacted the concrete barrier west of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was southbound in the second of two lanes. Vehicle 2 was southbound in the same lane ahead of V1. Vehicle 3 was southbound in the same lane ahead of V2. V3 and V2 began to slow for traffic and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 contacted the back of V3.

V1 and V2 were traveling in opposite directions, on the same roadway. V1 and V2 were both negotiating a curve. V1's front contacted V2's front. V1 then traveled off of the roadway on the left side and V1's front contacted a fence.

V1 was traveling south and V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V3 was traveling west on an intersecting roadway. V1 turned left at the intersection and V1's front contacted V2's front. V2 then traveled onto the intersecting roadway and V2's front contacted V3's left side.

V1 was traveling southbound on a five lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling westbound on a three lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a three lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling northbound on a six lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the intersection.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a six lane, two way roadway attempting to turn northbound onto a six lane, two way roadway.  While turning left at the intersection the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2.  The front of V2 then contacted a signpost.

Vehicle #2 was traveling Northeast on a two lane, two-way roadway entering a four legged intersection. Vehicle #1 was traveling Northwest on a two lane, two-way roadway entering the same sign controlled intersection as V2. V1 began to turn left and the front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1.
Vehicle #1 was traveling SW. Vehicle #2 was traveling SE on an intersecting road. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway in front of V1. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2.
V1 and V2 were both traveling westbound on the entrance ramp of a parkway with one lane of travel.  On this roadway, the frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane two of a one-way roadway with three lanes of travel.  V1 departed the roadway on the left side and its frontal plane contacted the guardrail. This caused V1 to rollover unknown times and come to final rest in lane three.
Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast.  The front of V1 contacted a bear in the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling northbound on one side of a median divided roadway, with two lanes with the same direction of travel, traveling in lane two. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.
V1 was negotiating a curve on a freeway interchange. V1 traveled off the roadway on the left side and the front impacted a tree.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound on an interstate. V1 was negotiating a lane change from the number 2 lane into the number 1 lane. V2 was occupying the number 1 lane. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two way road. The driver fell asleep and departed the roadway on the left side. V1 went down an embankment and rolled to the left three quarter turns, coming to rest on the passenger side.

V1 was traveling Southbound when it lost control and began to rotate counter-clockwise. V1 departed the roadway to the left, and the front end of V1 contacted a concrete divider. V1 then continued to rotate and the right side contacted the concrete divider.

Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound in the #2 lane. Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound in the #1 lane. Vehicle 1 attempted to cross the intersection heading southbound. Vehicle 2 front end made contact with Vehicle 1 right side. Due to Vehicle 2's speed Vehicle 1 spun counter clockwise and made contact with vehicle 2's left side with its right side. Vehicle 2 entered a counter clockwise rotation from this impact, departed the roadway on the right side and made contact with the light pole on the south east corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane 2 of a 2-lane on ramp.  V1 departed the roadway to the left, then overcorrected into a clockwise rotation, departing the roadway to the right.  V1 slid down an embankment, left side leading and the left side of V1 contacted a barb wire fence.  V1 then rolled over 4 quarter turns to the left, coming to rest on an adjacent roadway.

V1 was traveling east negotiating a left hand curve on a two way road with opposite traffic. V1 departed the road to the right, before traveling across both lanes to depart the road to the left. The front of V1 collided with an embankment. As V1 spun counterclockwise, the rear right collided with the embankment and V1 continued to spin back across the two lanes of the road. V1 departed the road to the right, traveled down another small embankment, the front of V1 collided with a barbed wire fence before coming to rest on all four wheels in a private field.

V2 was traveling north in the Number 2 lane of a eight-lane highway with four lanes of northbound traffic and four lanes of southbound traffic. V1 was in the southbound left turn lane attempting to turn left to proceed east on the intersecting roadway. The front of V2 collided with the right side of V1.

V2 was traveling eastbound on the Interstate in lane five and was about to overtake V1, which was traveling on the same trafficway in lane four.  V1 departed its lane on the left side and entered V2's path.  V2 sideswiped V1, then veered left, and sideswiped a section of guardrail in the median.  V1 fled the scene.

V1 was traveling northbound (exiting the Interstate) when it departed the roadway on the right side.  V2 was parked on the roadside of the exit.  The front end of V1 came into contact with the back end of V2's trailer.

Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound in the #2 lane and stopped to make a left hand turn onto a crossing street. Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound behind Vehicle 2 in the same lane. Vehicle 1's front made contact with Vehicle 2's rear.

V1 was pulling out from a business driveway attempting to turn left and head westbound. V2 was traveling eastbound approaching the driveway. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. After initial contact, the left side of V1 struck the right side of V2 in a side slap manner.

V1 was traveling westbound attempting a left hand turn at a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound approaching the same intersection. V1 turned in front of V2 and the front of V2 struck the front of V1. After initial impact V2 continued off the roadway eastbound where it struck a guardrail face. V3 was traveling south making a left turn to head east. After initial impact between V1 and V2 the front of V1 contacted the left side of V3.
V2 was stopped at an intersection facing east when V1 traveling east impacted the rear of v2 with frontal plane

V1 was traveling southeast in the left lane, entered the intersection and attempted a right turn. V2 was traveling south in the far right lane. V2 traveled into intersection. The front of V2 impacted with the left side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise. The left rear of V1 brushed against the right rear of V2 and came to an uncontrolled final rest in the intersection facing south. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to an uncontrolled final rest facing southeast.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane non-physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling west on a two lane non-physically divided roadway.  V2 traveled into intersection, V1 entered the intersection as well and attempted a left turn.  The front of V2 impacted with the right front of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest, V1 facing north and V2 facing west.

V1 was westbound on a 4 lane roadway approaching the intersection.  V2 was eastbound on the same roadway approaching the same intersection.  V2 began its left turn onto southbound lanes. The right front of V1 impacted with the right rear of V2.  V1 came to a controlled final rest facing westbound. V2 came to a controlled final rest facing southbound.

V2 was traveling east in lane 2 of a 6 lane undivided roadway. V1 was traveling behind v2 in the same lane. The front end of V1 contacted the rear end of V2. V1 came to a final rest in the initial travel lane, while V2 came to a final rest in lane 3.

V1 was headed north in lane 2 of the 5 lane undivided roadway (with left and right turn lanes) approaching a 4-way intersection. V2 was headed east in lane 1 of a 5 lane undivided roadway (with left turn lane) approaching the same intersection. V1 made contact with its left side to the front of V2, which then caused the right side of V2 to contact the left side of V1 in the intersection where they both came to final rest.

V1 was headed south on the two way undivided roadway. V2 was headed west on an intersecting 2 way undivided roadway. V1 made contact with its front end to V2's right side in the intersection. The force of the impact caused V1 to rotate clockwise 180 degrees and to the west, where it came to final rest in the NW corner of the intersection. V2 came to a final rest in its initial travel lane after impact.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way, non-divided roadway approaching a sign controlled three legged intersection. . V1 departed the roadway straight ahead at the intersection. V1 traveled through a tree line and onto a private drive. V1 contacted multiple trees and bushes before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane 2 of the westbound travel lanes of a four lane divided trafficway. V2 was traveling westbound in the same lane.  The front of V1 struck the front of V2 (Motorcycle) head-on.

V1 was traveling north on a straight roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and drove onto a raised median. The left side tires impacted with the concrete base of a light pole on the median. V1 drove over the median, crossed all lanes of the southbound roadway and departed the roadway to the east. The the left front wheel impacted a raised curb, causing further damage, before the front of V1 impacted a guard rail.

V2 was traveling west on a 4 lane one way roadway in lane 4 approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling in the same direction as V2 in lane 3. Before the intersection the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 then departed the roadway to the left side. The front of V2 impacted a metal light pole.
V1 was traveling east on the service road of a major highway. V2 was stopped ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 was south bound on a two lane non divided roadway, traveling though an intersection. V2 was north bound on a two lane non divided roadway approaching the intersection with V1. V1 entered the path of V2, where the frontal plane of V1 impacted the frontal plane of V2. V1 was pushed backward as a result of impact, causing V1 to roll over, with final rest being on its wheels. Occupant of V1 was ejected and received fatal injuries.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane 2 of a 3-lane physically divided roadway.  V2 and V3 were traveling southbound in lane 3 of the same roadway.  The left front wheel detached from V1 causing damage to the undercarriage.  The detached wheel then bounced over the center median where it contacted the left side of V2.  The wheel continued and contacted the top/windshield area of V3.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-divided roadway, V2 was traveling southbound on the same roadway. V1 made a left hand turn, V1s front plane struck V2s front plane.

V1 was traveling south bound on a two-way, two lane roadway.  V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted the ditch bottom.  V1 continued traveling within the ditch, striking the left side of the vehicle, while traveling up the right side of the ditch and completing a 1/4 turn onto its left side.  V1 re-entered the roadway, before coming to a final rest on its top.

Vehicles 1 & 2 were traveling southbound on an undivided, 2 lane roadway. Vehicle 1 was towing a trailer and pulled slightly onto the shoulder to make a left hand turn.  As Vehicle 1 turned left, the left front corner of Vehicle 1 collided with the right side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 was towed from the scene.
V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane road. V1 departed the left side of the lane onto a small median and impacted a pole with its frontal plane.
Vehicle 1 was westbound in the third of four lanes. Vehicle 2 was westbound in the third of four lanes behind V1. V1 slowed for traffic and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 and V2 were heading east on a two way two lane undivided roadway. V2 slowed down to turn south into a driveway. V1 did not slow down and struck V2 in its rear plane with its frontal plane. V2 then ran off the south side of the road striking a mailbox before coming to final rest in a ditch southeast of the driveway heading east. V1 came to final rest in the driveway heading east.

V1 was traveling west on a 4 lane divided highway towing a boat on a trailer. V1 failed to follow a curve in the roadway and left the right side of the roadway sideswiping a guardrail.  V1 then steered to the left crossing 2 lanes of roadway.  V1 then struck the left guardrail with the front of the vehicle. V1 then climbed over the guardrail imparting a clockwise rotation to the vehicle as it left the roadway.  V1 then rolled left and struck multiple trees and landed on its roof against a tree.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a three lane traffic way. Vehicle 2 was turning left at an intersecting road to travel east on the traffic way that Vehicle 1 was traveling on. Vehicle 2 turned left at the intersection and Vehicle 1's frontal plane struck the frontal plane of  Vehicle 2 at the intersection.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east, approaching a T-intersection. V1 departed the road at the top of the "T", into a grass area and impacted a garage with the front plane.

V1 was traveling eastbound, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge into a grass ditch. V1 entered a clockwise yaw then tripped and roll left two quarter turns; the rollover was interrupted by a impact to a fence.
V1 was exiting a private drive making a left turn. V2 was traveling east approaching the private drive. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east and Vehicles #2, #3, #4 and #5 were stopped, facing east. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2, then the front of V2 impacted the back of V3, then the front of V3 impacted the back of V4, then the front of V4 impacted the back of V5.

V1 was traveling north bound approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west bound approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and V1 contacted the front bumper on the left side of V2.

Vehicle #1 was stopped, facing north getting ready to exit a driveway. Vehicle #2 was traveling east. Both Vehicles entered the intersection and the front bumper of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 was turned clock-wise from the impact and contacted the right front wheel on a curb.

V1 was traveling eastbound on four lane one way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a two lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. V1's front contacted the left side of V2 in the intersection. V1 then proceeded eastbound and contacted a tree with its left side on a side walk.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way roadway approaching an intersection and V2 was traveling eastbound on a three lane roadway approaching the intersection. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1, then V1 departed the roadway, rolled over two quarter-turns and struck a sign post.

V1 was traveling westbound on a four lane two way roadway with a grass median. V1's LR tire tread separated from the rest of the tire. V1 departed the roadway to the left contacting the ground with the front of V1. V1 then rotated counter clockwise, then rolled six quarter turns, coming to final rest on it's top.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane two intending to take a left turn. V2 was traveling eastbound in lane one attempting to cross over the same intersection. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the front plane of V2. The right side plane of V1 then impacted the left side plane of V2. V2 then impacted a curb with its right front tire.
V1 and V2 were both traveling in the second lane of a four lane roadway heading northbound. The frontal plane of V2 impacted the rear plane of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a four lane roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in the third lane of a four lane roadway. V1 was attempting to take a left turn. The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling northbound on a highway. V2 was traveling at a slower speed due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.
V1 was negotiating a curve driving east. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. The impact caused V1 to rotate and rollover onto its roof.

V1 and V2 were traveling in the number 1 lane of a 5 lane interstate. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 went to the left across all lanes of traffic where the front of V2 impacted the center divider and rotated counter clockwise and the rear right of V2 impacted the center divider where the vehicle came to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two-way, two lane roadway. V2 was stopped in traffic ahead of V1, facing southbound, in the same lane. As a result, the front plane of V2 made contact with the rear plane of V1.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane roadway.  As V1 was traveling, a deer entered the roadway.  The front of V1 made contact with a deer.

V2 was traveling eastbound on a four lane physically divided roadway. V1 and V3 were eastbound merging from an exit ramp into the south lane of the road occupied by V2. V3 successfully merged onto the roadway. The left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2 causing damage. V1 continued off the south side of the roadway coming to final rest facing east. V2 continued east impacting the rear of V3 with the front plane causing damage. V2 became pinned between the semi and trailer of V3. V2 & V3 continued east 104 meters before coming to final rest with V3 facing east and V2 still pinned under V3 facing south.

V1 was traveling north approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped facing east at the intersection. V1 began to turn left and the front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. Both vehicles rotated and the right plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. The front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V3.
V2 was traveling south, stopped in traffic. V1 was also southbound on the same road. The front of V1 struck the rear of V2

V2 was east bound, stopped in traffic on a three lane, two way road. V2 was eastbound on this road. V1 attempted to avoid striking V2 by turning to the left. The right side of V1 struck the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane two of a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was also traveling on the same roadway in lane one.  On this roadway, V1 was attempting to turn right into a driveway and the rear plane made contact with the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. The driver of V1 suffered a medical emergency and departed the roadway on the right side. The frontal plane of V1 first made impact with a light pole and then the frontal plane of V1 made impact with a Utility Pole. V1 then returned to the original roadway and came to final rest in the left lane facing northeast.

V2 was traveling northbound in the left lane on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction and a two way left turning lane.
