Vehicle 1 was southbound negotiating a left curve. The driver of V1 lost directional control of the vehicle and began to rotate counterclockwise. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the back of V1 contacted a utility pole.
V1 and V2 were traveling westbound in the #2 lane on a 3 lane highway. V2 slowed down because of traffic and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was negotiating a curve traveling westbound on a 2 lane road in the number 1 lane. V1 departed the roadway to the right, its front right tire impacting the curb. The vehicle started a left side leading yaw, its left side impacting a pole, and striking a tree with its left rear side.  V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise and overturned four-quarter turns to the left before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V2, V3, and V4 were stopped heading east on the same roadway. The front plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. This caused a chain reaction where the front of V2 struck the rear of V3 and the front of V3 struck the rear of V4.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west.  A deer entered the roadway.  The left side of V1 contacted the deer.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided dirt roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right, its front plane contacting a ditch.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 2 lane of  a 3 lane without positive median barrier freeway. V2 ( medium heavy tractor trailer) was also traveling northbound, to the right of V1 traveling in lane 1. V1 departed its traffic lane to the right, its front end contacting the left front trailer tire of V2, causing V1 to overturn 8 quarter turns, leading left and landing on its wheels. V1 continued to travel backwards, departing the roadway to the left, crossing the median and all southbound traffic lanes, its back end contacting a guard rail before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound when it entered the northbound lane to overtake/pass a vehicle ahead of it.  V2 was traveling northbound.  V1 departed the roadway to avoid V2, but then returned to the roadway and collided with V2.  V1 came to rest on top of V2.

V1 was westbound on a two way, two lane road. V2 was legally parked on the north side of the road facing west. The front of v1 struck the rear of V2. V2 rolled to the left 2 quarter turns coming to rest on its top.
V1 was northbound approaching a four way intersection. V1 stopped at a stop sign and proceeded. V2 was was westbound on a two lane, two way road. The front of V2 struck the right side of V1.

Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a 2 lane roadway and had stopped behind a vehicle in front of it that was turning left onto another 2 lane roadway. Vehicle 1 was traveling west on the same roadway behind Vehicle 2 and it's frontal plane struck the rear plane of Vehicle 2.

V1 traveling north on a curved two-lane roadway and V2 was traveling on the same road in the opposite direction. V1's left rear tire separated from the vehicle and struck its left side (event 1). The wheel then crossed over the center line and impacted V2's front end (event 2).
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway.  V2 was traveling in the same lane, in front of V1.  V2 slowed for traffic ahead and the front of V1 made contact with the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a residential road. The front of V1 impacted an unknown non-fixed object in the middle of the road. V1 steered left where the front of V1 impacted a fence. V1 continued forward until the front of V1 impacted the side of a house.

V1 was traveling eastbound through an intersection. V2 was making a left hand turn through the same intersection, traveling westbound to southbound. In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the front end of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling westbound,attempting to make a left hand turn to continue north. Vehicle #2 was traveling westbound. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was negotiating a right curve on a two-lane undivided roadway with traffic in opposite directions. V1 departed the left side of the road, descended an embankment, and collided with a chain-link fence.
V1 was heading southbound on a seven-lane roadway, V2 was also heading southbound on the same roadway. V1 made a lane change and the front plane of V1 struck the right plane of V2.

V1 was traveling south, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue east. V2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. . Within the intersection, the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 started to rotate counter clockwise, leaving the roadway to the left, its front striking a light pole located on the raised center median.
Both Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were going southbound, in the same travel lane when Vehicle #2 decelerated for traffic ahead.  The frontal plane of Vehicle #1 struck the rear plane of Vehicle #2.

V1 was traveling south in lane 4 of divided roadway, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue east. V2 was traveling north in lane 3 of the same roadway. The front of V2 struck the right of V1 in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided trafficway after a heavy rain. As it approached a stop sign and began to brake at an intersection with a divided trafficway, the vehicle began to slide across the wet pavement into the intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane 2 of the divided traffic way, braked and slid on the wet pavement, and its frontal plane struck Vehicle 1's left side plane.

V1 was traveling West in lane 1 and V2 was traveling East in lane 2 on a four-lane divided roadway, which was wet at the time of the crash. V2 entered a counterclockwise rotation and departed the road on the left side entering the median then entered the eastbound number 2 lane where front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, non-divided highway. The driver of V1 steered right to avoid a child that entered the roadway. V1 exited the roadway to the right where the front end collided with a utility pole and then a mailbox, before coming to rest.

V1 was headed north in lane one of the two lane undivided roadway approaching a four-way intersection.  V2 was headed south on the same roadway also approaching the intersection.  V1 initiated a left turn at the intersection and made contact with its front end to V2's front end. V1 began a counter-clockwise yaw, and came to final rest south of the intersection.  V2 continued forward and off the road to the southwest apex of the intersection, where it made contact with its front end to a utility box and then a stump at which it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling North in lane 1 of a 2-way undivided roadway. V1 departed the road to the right and the front of V1 contacted a stone facade encasing a plastic drain pipe in a culvert. V1 then continued to travel north off the east road edge and the right side of V1 then contacted a utility pole. V1 then returned to the roadway traveling northwest across both travel lanes. V1 came to a final rest in a private drive facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east on a 2 lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection.  V1 departed the road to the left, entered into a counterclockwise yaw and rolled 8 quarter turns, right side leading.  V1 came to final rest in a field in the northeast corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 3 lane major highway in lane 2 approaching a two lane interchange ramp. V1 attempted to change lanes and exit to the interchange to the right. The front of V1 impacted a traffic attenuator

V1 was traveling westbound on a 4 lane divided roadway in lane 3 approaching an intersection to a private drive. V1 departed the lane to the left and drove onto the median. The front of V1 impacted a light pole.

V1 was traveling north on a highway. V2 was ahead of V1, stalled in the same lane of travel. V3 was traveling north in the lane to the left of V1 and V2. V4 was traveling south. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 started to rotate clockwise and V1 rotated counter clockwise. The left side of V2 impacted the right side of V1. The left side of V2 contacted the right side of V1 for the second time in a side swipe impact. V2 was propelled forward and into the lane to its left. The front of V3 impacted the rear of V2. After the impacts with V2, V1 continued to rotate counter clockwise, crossed all lanes of traffic to the left and departed the roadway to the left, crossing the grassy median. V1 entered the southbound lanes of the highway while still rotating counter clockwise. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V4.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south bound in lane three approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west bound in lane three approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front bumper of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated to the right and V2 rotated to the left which caused the right side of V2 to contact the left side of V1.
V1 was west bound on a two lane non-divided roadway, when a deer entered the roadway. V1's frontal plane impacted the deer.
V1 was traveling west on a divided highway when it departed the left (south) side of the road and its front impacted a tree.
V1, V2, and V3 were traveling West on a four-lane undivided roadway. V3 was stopped in roadway. V1 impacted the back of V2 causing the front of V2 to impact the rear of V3.
V1 was traveling Northbound on a two-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and impacted a tree with its frontal plane.

V1, V2, V3 and V4 were northbound in lane one, V2, V3, and V4 all stopped in the roadway.  V1 struck V2 from behind causing V2 to be pushed into V3, and V3 being pushed into V4. All vehicles came to final rest in the initial travel lane.

Vehicles #1 & #2 were traveling west on an undivided 4 lane street. Vehicle 1, traveling in the outside traffic lane, moved into the inside lane of traffic. As a result, the left side of Vehicle 1 collided into the right side of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles were towed from the scene.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane roadway, passing through an intersecting roadway. V2 was stopped at the same intersection, heading westbound. V1 passed the intersecting road, stopped, and drove southbound in reverse. V1's right side impacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a four-lane median divided roadway in the number 2 lane.  V1 departed the right side of the roadway and impacted a steel/concrete pole and a fire hydrant with the front. V1 then struck a shrub with the front.  V1 became airborne, entered into a clockwise yaw and contacted two building support posts with the left side.  V1 then contacted a metal fence with the undercarriage.  V1 continued in the yaw and the back plane contacted a brick wall of the building. V1 came to final rest inside the building.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane roadway stopped at stop sign.  V1 then proceeded to turn right at the intersection,   V2 was traveling  north on a two-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Upon entering the intersection, the front plane of V2 struck the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling east in the number 3 lane of a four- lane divided roadway.  V2 was traveling south in the number 1 lane of a three- lane intersecting roadway.  V3 was stopped for a traffic signal facing north in the number 2 lane of the three-lane roadway.  V4 was stopped for a traffic signal facing north in the number 1 lane of the three-lane roadway.   V1's front plane contacted the right side of V2.  This impact caused V1 to rotate clockwise, where V1's left side struck the left side of V3.  V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V2 contacted the front of V4.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a two lane divided highway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.
V1 and V2 were both eastbound on a two-lane roadway. V2 stopped waiting on westbound traffic to pass in order to turn left. The front of V1 collided with the back of V2.

V1 was northbound on a two-lane roadway. V1 departed the original travel lane to the left, then returned to the original travel lane crossing over it, departing the roadway to the right. The front of V1 then collided with a railroad arm support pole. V1 came to final rest at point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a three-lane, two-way street. V3 was traveling north on the same road in lane one. V2 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way street, approaching a T-intersection controlled by a stop sign. V2 attempted to make a left turn. The front of V1 impacted the left of V2 causing V2 to rotate counter-clockwise into the path of V3. The front of V3 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 was southbound on a five-lane undivided roadway attempting to make left turn onto an eastbound two-lane undivided roadway. After making the turn, V1 then departed its initial lane of travel to the left, departed the roadway to the left, and the front end of the vehicle impacted with a tree.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, non-physically divided roadway. V1 departed the initial travel lane to the left and into northbound lane impacting with a curb. V1 then steered to the right, which sent the vehicle into a clockwise rotation traveling back over the lane line to the right. The front tires of V1 departed the roadway and traveled onto a grassy area. The vehicle then skidded laterally and impacted with a mailbox. The left rear tire tripped at the road edge, causing V1 to begin a roll over sequence, leading with its left side. V1 made five quarter turns until ending with the left side on the ground. V1 continued sliding across a grassy area on its left side until impacting the roof with a utility pole, which caused the vehicle to rotate clockwise until the vehicle came to final rest facing north in the grassy area on the roadside.

V1 was traveling northbound in the right lane on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel northbound and one lane of travel southbound. V2 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway behind V1. V3 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway behind V2. As V1 approached the intersection, the frontal plane of V2 made impact with the rear plane of V1. Then the frontal plane of V3 made impact with the rear plane of V2.
V1 was traveling southbound on a three lane undivided roadway, attempting to make a left turn to continue east.  V1 departed the roadway to the right side and contacted trees with its frontal plane.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction.  V1 departed the roadway on the right side and contacted a wooden utility pole with its frontal plane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, negotiating a left hand curve, on a two lane, two way undivided roadway. V1 entered a counterclockwise yaw, departing its lane to the left, crossing the eastbound lane and departing the roadway to the left. V1 struck the embankment with its right side.
V1 was traveling north approaching a intersection attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling south approaching the same intersection. V1's right plane was contacted by V2's front plane.
V2 was leaving a parking lot and heading south across the intersection. V1 was traveling west crossing the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a one-way two lane roadway, V1 in the right hand lane, V2 in the left. V2 continued traveling south as V1 attempted a left hand turn to continue east.  The front of V2 struck the left side of V1. After the initial crash, V1's front struck a non-fixed object located on the right edge of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane undivided unmarked roadway through an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane undivided unmarked roadway through an intersection. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1 causing damage to both. V1 spun counter-clockwise and exited the north east side of the roadway and V2 came to final rest on the east side of the intersection.

V1 was southbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a line of shrubs and foliage and coming to final rest 12 meters south of the point of impact facing south.
V1 was headed eastbound on a two lane divided roadway, and an animal moved into V1's path from the right side.The animal struck the right side of V1.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound on a seven lane interstate in the number seven lane. V1 departed the lane to the right hand side and proceeded to depart the roadway right. V1 then returned to the roadway and crossed all lanes of traffic to the left, in a counterclockwise rotation, its front end impacting the front end of V2, which was still traveling in lane 7.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 2 lane of a 2 lane road while towing a trailer. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 2 lane of a 2 lane road. The trailer of V1 impacted the curb of the center median. The front of V1 impacted the curb. V1 traveled over the center median where the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 trailer rotated and impacted the left side of V2.

V1 was negotiating a curve traveling southbound on a two lane road in the number one lane. V1 departed the roadway on the left side and the front of V1 impacted a utility pole. After the impact V1 rotated clockwise and the left side of V1 impacted a fence.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided highway. V1 left the roadway on the right side. The right side of V1 contacted a barbed wire fence. The front of V1 struck a fence post. V1 continued through the fence causing damage to the left side of the vehicle. The undercarriage of V1 contacted surface rocks damaging the undercarriage.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a highway and approaching an exit ramp. The driver of V1 attempted to change lanes with the intention of exiting the highway. The exit lane was occupied by a non-contact vehicle. V1 was unable to enter the exit lane, departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted an impact attenuator.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound and approaching an intersection in a left turn only lane. The driver of V1 attempted to go straight through the intersection and departed the roadway on the north-east corner. The front of V1 contacted a signal pole.
V1 was traveling westbound on a four lane two way roadway with a grass median. The front of V1 struck a deer.
V1 and V2 were traveling southbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were traveling west, both in Lane 1 on a 4 lane trafficway with a positive barrier separating the east and west bound lanes. V1 was in front V2. V2's front plane struck the rear plane of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in Lane 4 of a divided roadway with 4 northbound lanes, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue west.  Vehicle #2 was traveling south in Lane 3 on the same roadway with 4 southbound lanes.  The front of V2 struck the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two way roadway. V1 entered into a counter-clockwise yaw, crossed over the eastbound lane and departed the roadway to the left where it rolled four quarter turns to the left.
V1 was traveling south on a 2-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the road to the left. The wheels of V1 contacted a curb, then the front end of V1 contacted a utility pole.
Vehicles #1, #2 and #3 were traveling northeast. V2 and V3 came to a stop at a stoplight, and the front  of V1 contacted the back  of V2, pushing it forward. The front of V2 contacted the back of V3.
V1 was west bound on a two lane non divided roadway, when a deer entered the roadway. V1's frontal plane impacted the deer.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane undivided roadway when it departed the roadway on the right. V1 returned to the roadway and began to rotate counterclockwise. V1 departed its lane, crossing over the westbound lane and departed the roadway on the left, rolling over (4 quarter turns, leading right). V1 came to rest against a chain link fence.
Vehicle 1 and 2 were traveling eastbound on a roadway. Vehicle 2 stopped for traffic. Vehicle 1's front end made contact with Vehicle 2's rear end.

Vehicle 1 was attempting to make a left hand turn onto the roadway from a private drive. Vehicle 2 was heading northbound in the #2 lane of a five-lane with a continuous left turn lane roadway. Vehicle 1's left side made contact with Vehicle 2's front end.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway with traffic in opposite directions. V1 departed its lane to the left and then the left side of the roadway and the front of V1 collided with a drainage culvert on the east side of the roadway. The collision with the culvert caused V1 to become airborne and rotate in such a fashion that the roof of V1 collided with a tree. The collision with the tree caused V1 to shear in half at a point just behind the front seats. The rear half of V1 came to final rest wrapped around the impacted tree. The front half of V1 continued south and collided with the ground coming to final rest in an agricultural field on its driver side facing in a westerly direction.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a five-lane, one-way street in lane three.  The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane 2 of the eastbound lanes of a two lane median divided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in lane 2 of the same roadway. The front of V1 Contacted the front of V2.  V1 then rolled 3 quarter turns to the right, coming to rest in the median.  V1 then caught fire.

Vehicle #1 was traveling East on a two-way, six lane, divided highway with an unprotected median as it approached an intersection. Vehicle #2, was traveling in the opposite direction on the same roadway and attempting to make a left turn at the intersection. Vehicle #1's frontal plane struck Vehicle #2's frontal plane. Vehicle #1 came to final rest with the front wheels up on the curb.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a 2 lane undivided road. V1 turned right into a private gravel driveway. An uninvolved 3rd vehicle had slowed behind V1 on the roadway while V1 made their turn. V2 was traveling north as well and was behind the uninvolved vehicle. V2 swerved off the right side of the road and crossed a grassy area impacting V1 on the right side with V2's front. This caused a secondary slap impact on the right side V1 vs left side of V2, and another impact as V1 rotated and struck a tree, hitting its left side. V2 then continued on veering right and hitting an embankment with its undercarriage.

V1 was traveling east on a five lane divided traffic way. V2 was traveling east on a three lane interstate exit ramp and was turning left to travel west on the five lane divided traffic way that V 2 was traveling on. As V2 was turning left at the intersection, its front struck the right side of V2.

V1 was southbound on two-lane roadway. V2 was parked on the east side of the two-lane roadway facing south. V3 was parked on the west side of the two-lane roadway facing south. V4 was parked in front of V3 on the west side of the two-lane roadway facing south. V1 departed the original travel lane on the left side. The left rear side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 then returned to the original travel lane and departed the original travel lane on the right side. The right side of V1 contacted the left side of V3. V1 continued southbound where the front of V1 then collided with the back of V4. V1 came to final rest after colliding with V4.
V1 and V2 were east on two lane undivided roadway.  V2 was stopped to make a left turn at the intersection and the front end of V1 made contact with the back end of V2.

V1 traveled north on a 2 lane undivided roadway attempting to turn left to continue westbound.  V2 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway approaching the intersection. The front end of V1 contacted the right side of V2.  The force of the impact caused V2 to depart the roadway to the right, where it struck a pole with its left side.
V1 and V2 were east on a three lane undivided roadway in lane one.  V1 was stopped for traffic. The front of V2 struck the rear plane of V1.

V1 was west bound on a two lane non divided roadway, when V1 attempted to avoid a deer. V1 started to loose control, and rotated counter clockwise as it left the road to the right. V1 impacted a drainage depression with the right plane. This caused the vehicle to rotate clockwise. V1 then impacted a large stone with its undercarriage. V1 impacted the embankment with its frontal plane.  V1 then impacted a tree with its frontal plane. This impact lifted the vehicle, and uprooted the tree. V1 then impacted an additional tree with its left plane, and impacted the ground with its right plane before coming to final rest leaning against the last tree.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, non-divided roadway. The driver of V1 was attempting to negotiate a sharp left curve as V1 departed the right side of the roadway. V1 impacted four (4) separate trees, mostly with the frontal plane, before coming to rest.

V1 was exiting an interchange, passing through an intersection, heading northbound. V2 was approaching the same intersection, heading southbound, on a two-way, two lane roadway. The front of V1 made contact with V2.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane, non-divided roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left side. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.
V1 was traveling south on a roadway approaching a roundabout. V2 was traveling in the roundabout. V1 entered the roundabout and its left side was impacted by the front V2.
V1 was traveling north on a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating the left hand curve. V1 departed the road to the right, impacting a small tree and a wire fence with the front plane.

V1 was traveling north on an entrance ramp to a two lane highway. V2 was traveling north on lane 1 of the two lane highway. As V1 attempted to merge onto the highway the front of V2 contacted the left side of V2. V2 then began to rotate counter clock wise across both lanes of the highway, and came to rest in the grassy median facing southbound.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane with grass median roadway, attempting to turn right to continue south. After turning right, V1 departed it's lane of travel to the left, crossed all travel lanes and departed the roadway to the left. V1 drove onto the raised median and impacted a light pole with its front.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side, striking a tree with its front end.
Vehicle #1, Vehicle #2, and Vehicle #3 were northbound on a two-lane undivided roadway. V1's front plane struck the rear plane of V2. V2's front plane then struck the rear plane of V3.

V1 was traveling south in lane 2 of a five-lane roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and continued off the roadway on the east side.  The LF wheel impacted a curb.  The front of V1 then impacted a tree.  V1 was redirected to the southwest and crossed all travel lanes, departing the west side of the roadway.  The RF wheel impacted a curb.  The front of V1 then impacted a tree.  V1 then rotated clockwise and rolled onto its left side.
V2 was stopped in traffic.  V1 was southbound traveling in the same lane.  V1 was traveling at a higher rate of speed.  The front end of V1 made contact with the back end of V2.

V1 and V2 were eastbound on the interstate. V2 was slowing for traffic ahead while traveling in the far right lane. V1 was traveling in the same lane. The front of V1 collided with the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest at point of impact.
V1 was driving northbound approaching an intersection, V2 was driving southbound approaching the same intersection. V1 made a left hand turn and the front plane of V1 impacted the front plane of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V2 was westbound on the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted a cow that was in the roadway. After impacting the cow, V1 traveled northeast and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.
V1 was traveling southeast approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped at the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane.
V1 was traveling northbound attempting to make a left turn. V2 was traveling southbound . V1's right plane was contacted by V2's front plane.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road that curved left. V1 steered left to avoid impacting an animal in the road and departed the left side of the road. V1 impacted several trees and the ground before coming to rest in a wetland area.

Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were traveling south on a three lane with continuous left turn lane roadway; V1 was ahead of V2. Vehicle #3 was traveling north on the same roadway. A non-contact vehicle slowed rapidly in front of V1, and V1 and V2 made unknown avoidance maneuvers. The front of V2 impacted the back of V1, then debris from the impact contacted an unknown plane of V3.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a four lane two way roadway with a grass median, V1 in Lane 2, V2 to the right of V1 in Lane 1. V1 began a clockwise yaw and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 then began a counterclockwise yaw, departed the roadway to the right, contacting a guardrail with it's right side. The left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in Lane 2 of a four lane, two way roadway attempting a left hand turn to continue north.  V2 was traveling westbound on the same roadway, in Lane 1.  The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two way two lane roadway. V2 was traveling westbound on a four lane two way roadway. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection.

V1 was stopped in the westbound lanes of a four-lane roadway attempting a left-hand turn. V2 was traveling westbound in the same lane when the front of V2 struck the rear of V1. After the initial impact, V2 traveled into the eastbound lanes where the front of V2 struck the front of V3.
V1 was traveling North on a two lane two-way roadway.  V2 was legally parked facing North on the right side of the same roadway when the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling east on a 4 lane highway in the number 3 lane. V2 was stopped due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling eastbound on a 4 lane interstate in the number 3 lane. V4 was traveling eastbound in the number 2 lane. V5 was traveling eastbound in the number 4 lane. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 started to rotate counter clockwise and the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3. V2 continued to rotate counter clockwise into the number 2 lane where the right of V2 impacted the left side of V4. V2 continued rotating counter clockwise towards the number 4 lane where the front of V5 impacted the right side of V2. V2 departed the travel lanes and the rear of V2 impacted a concrete traffic barrier and came to rest.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the east side of the roadway traveling down and embankment and striking rocks with the front and undercarriage causing damage. After the initial impact V1 became airborne in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 traveled roughly 16 meters before landing and overturning right side leading 4 quarter turns. V1 came to final rest facing northwest on top of a pile of wood.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south. V1 departed the road to the right and the right side of V1 contacted a tree. V1 continued off road and the front plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise and re-entered the roadway backwards, then came to rest just off the road to the left.

V2 was traveling west in the first lane of a two lane roadway. V1 was traveling behind V2 headed west in the first lane. V2 braked to avoid a collision with another vehicle that crossed in front of it's path. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling on a two lane roadway heading north. V1 attempted to make a right turn to travel southbound but lost control. The right side plane of V1 impacted the guardrail face. V1 came to rest at guardrail facing north.

V2 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane roadway entering the rotary (roundabout). V1 was traveling westbound in the same lane behind V2. The front plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling eastbound attempting to make a left hand turn to continue north.  Vehicle #2 was traveling west on the same roadway.  The front plane of V2 struck the right plane of V1.  Subsequently, the RF wheel of V1 struck an unknown object.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two-lane undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling east on the intersecting two-lane undivided roadway roadway. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.  The vehicles rotated toward each other and the left of V1 contacted the right of V2 in a second impact.  V1 departed the road to the right, its left side contacting a utility marker.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way road. V2 was legally parked on the south side of this road facing east. The front of V1 struck the rear of V2.
V1 was westbound on a three lane, two way road approaching an intersection. V2 was northbound on a five lane road approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 struck the right side of V2.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling southbound on a physically divided roadway. Vehicle 1 was traveling in the #3 lane. Vehicle 2 was traveling in the #4 lane. Vehicle 1 attempted to merge over into the #4 lane. Vehicle 1's left side made contact with vehicle 2's right side.

V1 was traveling Westbound on an interstate when it departed the roadway to the right. The front end of V1 contacted a sign post. V1 continued westbound and the front end of V1 contacted a guard rail. V1 then overturned 4 quarter turns, leading left before coming to final rest on an off-ramp.

V1 was traveling westbound on a five-lane with continuous turn lane. V2 was traveling southbound on a two-lane undivided intersecting roadway, attempting to make a right hand turn to continue west. Tthe front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling east, negotiating a slight right curve, in the number two lane of a four lane roadway composed of two eastbound travel lanes and two westbound travel lanes separated from each other by a raised concrete curb and a dirt/grass median. V2 was traveling in the number two westbound lane on the same roadway. V1 departed the left side of the roadway onto a dirt grass median, the front of V1 struck a sign supported by a metal pole in the median. V1 traveled north in a counter clockwise yaw, across the median and re-entered into the number two westbound lane of the roadway. The front of V2 collided with the right side of V1. The collision with V1 caused V2 to rotate clockwise approximately 180 degrees. V2 came to final rest facing northeast in the number one westbound lane of the roadway. After colliding with V2, V1 continued to travel north and came to final off the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane one of a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction and a left turn lane.  V2 was traveling on the same roadway in lane two.  V1 departed this roadway on the right side and contacted a street sign pole and a tree with its right frontal plane.  V1 then entered back onto the roadway and contacted V2's right side plane with its left side plane.

V1 was traveling northbound in the right lane on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling southbound in the left lane on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction, Attempting to make a left hand turn to continue east. The front plane of V2 struck the left plane of V1. After the initial impact, V1 traveled forward and the front plane of V2 struck the left plane of V1.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a five lane with continuous turn lane roadway, V2 ahead of V1.  V2 (M/H truck with trailer) was making a U-turn from westbound to eastbound.  The front end of V1 came into contact with the back end of V2's trailer. V1 departed the roadway to the right, its front/right wheel striking the curb.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane 2 of a non-positive barrier roadway with four southbound lanes. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane 1 of the crossing non-positive barrier roadway with three westbound lanes. The front end of V2 struck the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, roadway passing through the same intersection.  The front of V1 made contact with the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in the # 2 lane of a 5 lane with a continuous left turn lane roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the # 2 lane on the same roadway. V2 departed the lane to the left and attempted to return to their side of the road when the front of V1 impacted the left of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound on a 2-lane undivided roadway attempting to turn left at an intersection.  V2 was traveling westbound in lane 1 of 4-lane not physically divided roadway attempting to crossover the same intersection.  The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.
V2 was traveling east in lane 1 of a three lane divided roadway when it slowed due to traffic ahead. V1 was traveling behind V2 in the same lane when V1's front plane struck 2's rear plane.

Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a five lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a three lane intersecting roadway and was crossing the five lane roadway. While crossing the intersection, Vehicle 1 was struck on the right front side plane by Vehicle 2's frontal plane. Vehicle 1 then rotated and its rear right side plane struck Vehicle 2's left side plane. Vehicle 1 then struck a curb, departed the roadway, and struck a sign and utility marker on the right side plane of the vehicle.
V1 was turning left onto a four lane roadway from a business drive facing south. V2 was traveling west in lane 2 on the four lane roadway. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.
V1 was traveling south on a two-lane roadway towing a trailer, V2 was traveling northon the same roadway. The front plane of V2 impacted the front on V1 towing trailer.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane (one-way) roadway. The frontal plane of V1 impacted a deer that entered the roadway from the left.

V1 was traveling south on a rural three-lane roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. Both vehicles approached an intersecting road and V1 initiated a left turn.  V1's right plane was contacted by V2's front plane. V2 was towing a trailer.

V1 was traveling south on the two lane undivided roadway approaching a four-way intersection.  V2 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection.  V1 made contact with its front end to the right side of V2 in the intersection.  The force of the impact caused V1 to initiate a clockwise yaw and it departed the road at the SW apex of the intersection where it came to final rest.  V2 also departed the SW apex of the intersection where it came to final rest off the road.
V1 was traveling south in lane 2 of 3 of a 6 lane divided Interstate roadway when it departed the road to the left and contacted a cable barrier with the front end.
V2 was traveling east in lane 1 of a 2 lane undivided roadway.  V1 was attempting to exit a private drive. The front end of V1 struck the right side of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north bound on a driveway attempting to turn east. Vehicle #2 was traveling east bound in lane three. Vehicle #3 was stopped, facing east, in lane four. V1 traveled north from the driveway and the left side of V1 was impacted by the front bumper of V2. V1 then traveled north and the front bumper of V1 impacted the right side of V3.

V1 was traveling west on a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 ran out of its lane to the right then left the road on the right in the curve of the road. V1 then ran across a grass median at a 3 way intersection, gouged the asphalt with the undercarriage as he crossed a perpendicular adjoining roadway shoulder, then V1 left the right side of that roadway and struck a metal stop sign post. V1 continued up the embankment behind the post and struck a tree behind the RF tire with the right underside of the car, V1 began to rotate with the slope of the bank as it climbed the slope and rode up the tree, then striking another tree with the undercarriage rotated past 1 quarter turn. V1  then rolled onto its top and then slid on its top along the slope and launched off of a 2.02m retaining wall, landing on the shoulder and roadway onto its hood and roof.

V1 and V3 were traveling in the same lane, lane 1, on a 3 lane access road. V2 was parallel to these vehicles in the second lane. V3 was at a stop. V2 entered lane 1 over right lane line. V2 struck V1's front end with an unknown plane. V1 veered right, departed the roadway to the right,  its RF Tire impacting the curb. V1 traveled off of the roadway and then back on. V1's front end and V2's rear end made contact.
V1 and V2 were both northbound in the same lane of the same roadway. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.
V1 was pulling out of parking lot. V2 was west bound on a 2 lane non divided roadway.  V1's left plane was struck by V2's frontal plane.

V1 was traveling north bound on a 4 lane highway approaching a bridge in lane 2. V1 lost control departed the lane to the right, then departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted the concrete barrier on the bridge.

V2 was traveling westbound on a four lane major highway in lane one. V1 was traveling the same direction on the same roadway as V2 in lane three. V2 departed the roadway to the right side and drove onto the grassy embankment. V2 then returned to the roadway from the right side, crossed lane one, two and entered lane three. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 continued across lane three and lane 4 then departed the roadway and impacted the traffic attenuator with it's front.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling south on a 2 lane divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was stopped in traffic. The front of Vehicle 1 collided into the back of a trailer which was being towed by Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 was towed from the scene.

V1 was traveling north west on a five lane non-physically divided roadway in the first lane. V2 exited a private driveway and turned left onto roadway, crossed over three lane lines and a double yellow lane line into lane one. The front of V2 impacted with the left front of V1. V1 came to final rest in it's original lane facing north west. V2 came to final rest facing north west straddling the double yellow lane.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, two lane street. V1 departed the right side of the road and stuck a guardrail and bridge abutment with its front plane causing it to rotate clockwise. V1 came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way, two-lane roadway ascending a hill. V2 was legally parked in a driveway perpendicular to the road. V1 stopped for an animal in the road and began to roll backwards down the hill. V1 departed the left side of the road and impacted a rock wall with the back plane.  V1 back then contacted the right side of V2.  V1 left then contacted the right side of V2 two separate times.  V1 back then contacted a shrub, and a tree.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane unmarked undivided roadway. V1 departed the left side of the travel lane continuing off the left side of the roadway before striking a tree with the front plane and coming to final rest at the point of impact facing east.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane marked not physically divided roadway. V2 was eastbound stopped at a traffic light. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2 causing damage.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane one way roadway that developed into a three lane roadway at a northbound exit ramp. V1 began to take the exit by merging into the exit lane but then attempted to return to its initial travel lane. A small animal crossed V1's path of travel. V1 departed  the roadway to the left, striking an embankment with its front plane. V1 then struck a bush before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane two way undivided roadway. V2 was headed west on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left, crossing the centerline, its front plane striking the frontal plane of V2. V1 departed the roadway to the left and struck a mailbox. V1 continued off the roadway striking a tree before coming to final rest. After contact with V1, V2 departed the roadway to the right, striking a mailbox with its right side, before coming to final rest.

V2 was stopped in the first lane of a two lane roadway headed west and attempting a left turn into a parking lot. V1 was traveling westbound behind V2 in the same lane. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were traveling westbound in the first lane of a three lane roadway. V2, V3, and V4 were fully stopped for a traffic signal. The front plane of V1 then impacted the rear plane of V2. This resulted in the front plane of V2 impacting the rear plane of V3, and the front plane of V3 then impacting the rear plane of V4.
V1 and V2 were traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane road. V2 stopped for traffic. The front end of V1 impacted the rear end of V2.

V1 was traveling northeast on a 6 lane highway in lane 6. V2 was traveling northeast on a 6 lane highway in lane 5. V1 departed the roadway to the left and corrected back onto the roadway and crossed the lane line on the right where it impacted the left side of V2.  V1 continued and departed the roadway on the left side and impacted a guardrail.  V1 returned back to the roadway, crossed all 6 lanes and departed the roadway on the right side where it impacted a post and a tree.

V1 and V3 were traveling southbound on a 5 lane interstate in the number 1 lane. V2 was traveling southbound to the left of V1 and V2, in the number 2 lane. V1 changed lanes to the left and the front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. V2 moved left into the 3 lane and then back into the number 1 lane, where the front of V2 impacted the left of V3.

V1 was traveling westbound out of a private parking lot and attempting to make a left turn to go southbound. V2 was traveling northbound in the right lane on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. The front plane of V1 struck the front plane of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in the left turning lane of a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction attempting to turn left heading southbound.  V2 was traveling eastbound in lane two of the same roadway.  The front plane of V2 contacted the right side plane of V1.

V1 was westbound on two-lane interstate in the northern lane. V2 was westbound on the same two-lane interstate in the southern lane. V1 merged into V2's lane. The front of V2 collided with the left side of V1. V1 was pushed by V2 resulting in V1 to begin rolling. V1's trailer detached from the hitch and traveled to its final rest position. V1 rolled 4 quarter turns coming to final rest in the median between the eastbound and westbound travel lanes facing eastbound. V2 came to final rest on the edge of the westbound roadway.

V1 was driving westbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 struck a utility pole.  The front of V1 then struck an embankment and rolled two quarter turns.
V1 was heading eastbound in lane 3 of a divided roadway with four eastbound lanes. V1 departed the roadway to the left, its front end striking the guardrail.

V1 was traveling south on a four lane, two way roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 struck a small signpost.  The left side of V1 then contacted a utility pole.  V1 then rolled four quarter turns, right side leading and the right side of V1 contacted a large tree while rolling over.
V1 was south bound on a two lane non divided roadway when a deer entered the roadway. V1 impacted the deer with its frontal plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a slight left curve. V1 departed the road to the right and overcorrected. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise, reentered the road, crossed the centerline and the northbound lane and departed the roadway to the left. V1 traveled up an embankment and tripped over eight quarter turns to the right. During the roll, V1's right side contacted a sign post.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a three lane undivided roadway attempted to turn left into a parking lot. Vehicle #2 was traveling south on the same roadway. the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.

Vehicle 2 was northbound and approaching an intersection in a left turn lane. Vehicle 1 was stopped facing south at the same intersection. While making the left turn, V2 departed its travel lane on the right side. The front of V2 contacted the front of V1.
Vehicle 1 was eastbound in lane 1, approaching a left curve. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted a light pole.
V1 was traveling eastbound negotiating a left curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and struck a garbage can. V1 then departed the left road edge and the front plane contacted and tree.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way road approaching a four-legged sign controlled intersection. V2 was eastbound on a two lane, two way road approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V1 struck the right side of V2. V2 rolled 6 quarter turns coming to rest its left side.

Vehicles #1 and #3 were traveling south.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north on the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Debris from the impact of V1 and V2 contacted the left side of V3.  V2 then yawed clockwise on the roadway and tripped into a left side leading rollover.  V2 rolled one quarter turn to the left, coming to rest facing east straddling the east road edge.

V1 was traveling from eastbound to northbound on a cloverleaf on-ramp entrance to the Interstate.  V2 was traveling northbound on the main portion of the Interstate, and was approaching the merge point of the on-ramp.  V1 departed the roadway on the left and traversed the downward sloping embankment separating the on-ramp from the main portion of the Interstate.  V1 then entered the roadway into V2's path.  The front end of V2 came into contact with the left side of V1.  V1 rotated clockwise and its front end then end-swiped the concrete median barrier.

V1 was traveling Northbound on an interstate roadway, in lane 2. V2 was also traveling Northbound, in front of and to the right of V1 in lane 1. V1 departed its lane to the right, and the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V1 then departed the roadway on the left, striking three large rocks. V1 then overturned 4 quarter-turns, leading right. V1 struck a fourth large rock, then came to rest in the center median.
V1 was traveling westbound when it departed the roadway on the left and overturned (5 quarter turns - leading right).

V1 was traveling east in lane 3 of a divided roadway with three eastbound lanes, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue south. V2 was traveling north in lane 1 of a divided roadway with two northbound lanes. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west, approaching an intersection and Vehicle #2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning left; V2 entered the intersection going straight, and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. After impact, the vehicles rotated in opposite directions and the left side of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane 2 on a one-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on the crossing two lane undivided roadway. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was southbound on a two-lane roadway. V2 was eastbound on a two-lane roadway. V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The front of of V2 collided with the right side of V1. V1 and V2 came to final rest at POI.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 2 lane, one way street. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the intersecting, 3 lane, one way street. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of Vehicle 1 collided into the right side of Vehicle 2.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a three lane, median divided roadway.  V2 was traveling behind V1 in the same lane.  V1 was slowing for traffic and the front of V2 made contact with the rear of V1.
V1 was traveling south behind V2 in the Number 1 lane of a three lane limited access roadway. The front of V1 collided with the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a 2 lane undivided roadway when it departed the right road edge. V1 steered left, crossed both lanes and departed the left road edge.  V1 steered right, crossed both lanes and departed the right road edge while rotating clockwise where its left side contacted a tree.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise and contacted a sidewalk edge with its right front wheel and came to rest.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 sustained a control loss, entered a clockwise yaw, and rolled over to the left one quarter-turn.

V1 and V2 were southbound on a three lane divided interstate. V2 departed the initial travel to the right. The right front of V2 collided with the left side of V1. V1 disconnected from V2, departed its travel lane to the left to cross over 2 lanes of traffic and impacted with a Jersey barrier. V2 came to final rest at second point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two lane, two way roadway. As vehicle 1 negotiated a curve in the road, the vehicle lost control and exited the roadway on the right side. The vehicle traveled a short distance in a grass field with a drainage ditch before returning to the roadway. The vehicle then traveled across both lanes of traffic and departed the left side of the roadway. The vehicle traveled down an embankment where the front contacted a tree.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a 2 lanes lightly curved to the left, non-divided roadway, V2 was traveling south on the same roadway in lane one. V1 entered the southbound lane while negotiating the curve. V1 reentered the northbound lane, while V2 also entered the northbound lane in an attempt to avoid the crash. V1's front contacted V2's front. At final rest both vehicles were partially blocking both travel lanes.

Vehicle #1 was going westbound at a controlled intersection and was making a left turn onto a four lane non-divided roadway. Vehicle #2 was going northbound on the four lane roadway when Vehicle #1's frontal plane contacted Vehicle #2's frontal plane.

Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were both traveling North on a six lane, positively divided highway. Vehicle #1 ran off the right side of the roadway striking a guard rail. Vehicle #1 then crossed back across the highway to the left and struck Vehicle #2 in the right side causing Vehicle #2 to lose control and overturn in the roadway coming to final rest on its top. Vehicle #1 then struck the concrete barrier on the left side plane before coming to final rest.
V1 and V2 were traveling southbound on a two-lane undivided roadway. V1's front plane impacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on the intersecting two-way, two-lane roadway passing through the intersection when the front plane of V1 contacted the right side of V2. After initial contact with V2, V1 continued south, departed the right curb where it struck a guy wire with its right plane before coming to final rest.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a three-lane, divided highway in lane #2. V1 was traveling behind V2 when the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. After initial contact, V1 traveled off the roadway to the right contacting a guardrail face then traveled to the left where it struck a concrete barrier.

V1 traveling south on two way one lane dirt road when a deer entered from the left. V1 swerved to miss deer and lost control.  V1 departed the roadway on the right side.  V1 rolled over to the left and impacted a street sign with its top plane during the rollover.  V1 came to rest on the west roadside on its wheels.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a 2-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and began to rotate counter-clockwise. V1's right side struck two mailboxes and returned to the roadway from the right side. V1 departed the lane on the left and then departed the roadway on the left and began to rotate clockwise. V1 then rolled left three quarter turns before coming to final rest.

V2 was traveling north in lane 1 of a 2 way undivided roadway approaching a T-intersection, and slowed down with the intent of turning left.  V1 was traveling in the same lane directly behind V2 and the front end of V1 contacted the rear end of V2.  The force of the impact caused V2 to rotate counter-clockwise into lane 2 of southbound traffic in which V3 was traveling.  The front end of V3 contacted the right side of V2 which forced V2 to depart the roadway to the south west corner of the intersection and strike a fence with its front end.

V1 was traveling northbound attempting to crossover an intersection.  V2 was traveling southbound on same roadway attempting to turn left at the same intersection.  In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling south in the second lane of a seven lane, two way roadway, divided by a median, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling westbound on a one way three lane roadway, approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. After impact V1 traveled southwest and the front of V1 contacted a fire hydrant.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south and departed the road to the left over a curb and onto a grass median. V1 impacted a large tree with an unknown plane, then sustained a rollover event and came to rest on the top plane.
V1 was traveling south on a two-lane undivided roadway towards a roundabout. V1 departed the roadway straight ahead, striking a large boulder and then a utility box with its front end.

V1 was traveling south, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and V2 clockwise. Both vehicles impacted again in a side slap impact. V1 continued to move into a southeast direction and departed the roadway onto a raised median. The front of V1 impacted the pole of a traffic light. The pole broke off and fell on top of V1.

V1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling south in the number one lane of a two lane divided highway. V1 left original travel lane and ran off the left side of the road, yawed and the left side of V1 made contact with the cable barrier. V1 then over corrected back to the right, returned to the roadway, departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 made contact with a cement barrier, sideswiping down the right side of the vehicle.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway. A deer entered the roadway. The front of V1 impacted the deer.

Vehicle 1 was stopped at an intersection intending to travel in a westerly direction. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on the intersecting 5 lane roadway. Vehicle 3 was traveling south on the 5 lane roadway. As Vehicle 1 crossed the intersection, the left side of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Then, the left side of Vehicle 1 contacted the left side of Vehicle 3. Vehicles 1 & 2 were towed from the scene.
V1 was traveling west on a 2-lane undivided roadway.  The driver of V2 was southbound on the crossing 4-lane undivided roadway.  The front end of V2 made contact with the right side of V1.
V1 and V2 were southbound  on a two lane undivided roadway, V2 attempting to make a left hand turn to continue west. V1's front plane struck the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling east in lane 3.  V1 departed the roadway to the left, its front end impacting the left guardrail face. Due to impact forces, V1 proceeded to skid laterally back onto roadway, crossing over three traffic lanes and departed the roadway to the right. The rear plane of V1 impacted a concrete wall and came to an uncontrolled final rest facing north.

V1 was traveling northeast in the first lane on a three lane non- physically divided roadway with a two way left turn lane. V2 was backing out of a private driveway onto the roadway and into the first lane. The back of V2 impacted with the right side of V1. V1 traveled over left lane line then back over left lane line into original lane. V1 continued to travel over the curb, grassy strip, sidewalk and into a private front yard where V1 came to an uncontrolled final rest. V2 came to a final rest facing east with the rear of vehicle in the right southbound lane and the front of the vehicle in the two way left turn lane.

V1 was southbound on a three lane undivided roadway. V2 was eastbound on the crossing one-way off-ramp roadway. The left front of V1 impacted with the right front of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest facing southeast.

V1 was northbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 attempted to make a right turn and departed the roadway left, traveling down an embankment. The undercarriage of V1 struck the ground while traveling down the embankment. V1 came to final rest off the north side of the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction attempting to turn left heading southbound.  V2 was legally parked and unoccupied along the north-side roadway facing westbound.  The frontal plane of V1 contacted the left side plane of V2.  This caused V1 to rollover 1-quarter turn onto its left plane.

V1 was traveling northbound in the right lane on a divided two way roadway with four lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling in the same direction and on the same roadway in front of V1. As both vehicles were approaching an exit ramp, the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 continued to make impact with the left plane of V2, and started to rotate clockwise. After the initial impact, V2 also started to rotate clockwise, departed roadway on the right side  and the rear plane of V2 made contact with a concrete barrier. V1 also departed the roadway on the right side and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the same concrete barrier.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two-way, two lane roadway.  A deer entered the roadway and the front of V1 made contact with the deer.

V1 was westbound on two-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was northbound on a two-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V2 collided with the left side of V1. V1 then went off the roadway to the right, striking a street sign with the front, before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling west through an intersection on a three-lane, two-way street. V2 was traveling north on a three-lane, two-way road, through the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2 and spun around clock-wise coming to rest in the intersection. V2 departed the left side of the road and impacted a building with its front plane.
V1 was traveling south on a two-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling westbound on a single lane roadway. V2 and V3 were both parked, not in transport and facing west. V1 departed the roadway to the left, its left side striking V2 on the right front side. The frontal plane of V1 then impacted the rear plane of V3 and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 swerved to avoid an animal in the roadway, departed the roadway to the right and impacted a utility pole with its frontal plane and again with its right rear side. V1 then impacted a rock wall with its frontal plane before coming to final rest.

V1 and V2 were both traveling southbound in lane 2. V2 was ahead of V1. V1 departed its lane to the right and began to rotate counter clockwise, its front plane and then left plane contacting the right side on V2. V1 departed the right side of the roadway, its rear plane contacting a tree and the right plane contacted another tree before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 4-lane, one-way road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound approaching the intersection on a 5-lane, one-way road. The front of V2 struck the right side of V1. After the first impact the right side of V2 struck the left side of V1 in a side slap manner. V2 continued south and departed the roadway right, where the front plane struck a light pole.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound on a two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling west bound on the same roadway. V2 departed the lane on the left side, its front striking the left side of V2. V1 then departed the roadway on the right side and rolled over to the left four quarter turns.
V1 was making a left turn out of a business driveway intending to travel south. V2 was traveling south in lane 2 on a five lane roadway when the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.
V1 was traveling South on a 2 lane undivided roadway.  A deer entered the roadway from the right and V1's front end contacted the deer.

V1 was headed south in lane two of a six lane undivided roadway.  V2 was headed north in lane four of the same roadway and was in the left turn lane to head west.  V1 made contact with its front end to the front end of V2 in the intersection.  V1 then departed the road to the southwest apex of the intersection where it came to final rest.
V1 was traveling behind V2 in lane 1 of a 3 lane divided trafficway.  As traffic began to slow, the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2.

V1 traveling east on a two lane two way undivided roadway.  V1 departed its lane on the left and continued to travel off the roadway on the left side. V1 's front right contacted a tree causing V1 to rotate clockwise where the front left contacted a tree causing V1 to then rotate slightly counterclockwise into a tree with the right side of V1 before coming to final rest.
Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were traveling north, on a two lane undivided roadway, V2 ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 and V2 were southbound on three-lane roadway. The front of V1 collided with the back of V2 (event 1). Due to road conditions, V2 driver lost control of the vehicle resulting in a clockwise rotation. As V2 rotated, it departed the roadway to the left. V2 came to final rest with the back of the vehicle against a utility pole facing northbound (event 3) after traveling 97 meters from event 1. After the initial impact with V2, the driver of V1 lost control of the vehicle due to road conditions. V1 began a clockwise rotation traveling 195 meters southbound and coming to final rest with its left side against a utility pole (event 2).

V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane non-divided roadway while raining. V1 departed its lane on the left side, began to rotate counter-clockwise, and  departed the roadway on the left side. After departing the roadway, the vehicle traveled down an embankment, struck a tree with the front of the left side plane of the vehicle, struck the ground with the undercarriage of the vehicle, and struck the same tree with the rear of the left side plane of the vehicle.  The vehicle then rotated counter-clockwise and struck 2 fence posts with the right side plane of the vehicle before coming to final rest.

V1 was towing a vehicle on a car dolly and traveling east in lane one on a two lane divided highway. V1 lost control and began to yaw left side leading near the north road edge. V1 tripped and rolled left side leading, coming to rest straddling lane two of eastbound travel and the north road edge. The vehicle it was towing came to rest off the north road edge after becoming dislodged from V1.

V1 and V2 were both traveling northbound in adjacent lanes approaching an intersection. At the intersection a non contact vehicle attempted to turn  into the lane V1 was traveling in. V1 departed the lane to the right, and impacted the left side of V2 with it's right side. V2 then rotated counter clockwise and departed the lane to the left. V2 then departed the roadway to the left into the raised median and impacted a tree with its left side.

V1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V2 attempted to make a U-turn. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 began a counter clockwise yaw and rolled 5 quarter turns, right side leading, before departing the road to the south.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way roadway entering a sign controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way roadway entering the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. After the initial impact, V1 departed the roadway and contacted a utility pole with its frontal plane before coming to rest. V2 came to rest on the shoulder facing south.

V1 was southbound on a 4 lane undivided roadway in lane 1. V1 departed the roadway to the right due to a non-contact vehicle. V1 impacted the curb with its right front tire before the right plane of V1 impacted with two utility poles then was redirected onto the roadway. V1 departed the southbound lanes to the left, crossed over the northbound lanes and departed the roadway on the left. The front of V1 collided with a fire hydrant displacing it before coming to final rest against a landscaping rock wall.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane 2 of a 3 lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve.  V2 was traveling eastbound on same roadway.  V1 departed the lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on an undivided 2 lane road. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on that same road. Vehicle 3 was stopped at the intersecting road, facing south. Vehicle 1 initiated a left hand turn at the intersection. The front of Vehicle 2 collided into the right side of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 spun in a clockwise rotation and the back of Vehicle 1 collided into the front of Vehicle 3. Vehicle 2 left the right side of the road and collided into a utility pole and guy wire.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel and a left turn lane in each direction entering a four-legged light controlled intersection.  V2 was traveling east on the intersecting two-way roadway with a single lane of travel and a left turn lane in each direction entering the same intersection.  In the intersection the frontal plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1.  After impact, V1 departed the roadway to the right, its front plane striking a light pole located on the northeast corner before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the fourth lane of two way divided highway with four lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling in the same direction in the same lane behind V1. V3 was traveling in the same direction in the same lane behind V2. The frontal plane of V3 made impact with the rear plane of V2. Then the frontal plane of V2 made impact with the rear plane of V1.

V4 was stopped in the eastbound lane on a 2 lane undivided roadway, waiting to make a left hand turn. V3 and V2 were also stopped behind V4. V1's front end made contact with the back end of V2 causing V2's front end to make contact with the rear of V3 and the front of V3  to make contact with the rear of V4.
V1 was northbound on a two lane undivided roadway when a deer ran into the roadway. The front of V1 impacted the deer.

V1 was northbound on a five lane divided roadway exiting onto a two lane ramp. V1 departed the roadway to the right impacting with the concrete wall. V1 returned to the roadway to the left, departed both travel lanes to the left, then the roadway to the left. The left side of V1 impacted with the impact attenuator, and continued on, the front then impacting with the concrete traffic barrier, where it came to final rest.

V1 was heading eastbound in the first lane of a two lane, one way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side, impacting a curb with its frontal plane. V1 then impacted a light pole and a fire hydrant with its frontal plane, before it came to final rest.
V1 and V2 were traveling southeast on a 3-lane without positive median roadway, with V1 ahead of V2. V2's front plane contacted V1's rear plane.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection to turn left. After completing the left turn, the driver of V1 departed the vehicle in the roadway and fled the scene. The vehicle was left in gear and began to roll, departing the roadway to the left and striking the curb.

Vehicle 1 was westbound in the second of five lanes. V1 departed the travel lane on the left side, crossed through all lanes and departed the left side of the roadway. The front of V1 contacted the concrete traffic barrier.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road that curved left. V2 was traveling in the opposite direction. The left side of V1 impacted the front of V2 causing both vehicles to rotate counter-clockwise. V2 impacted the curb on the eastbound lane with its front right tire.

V1 was following V2 on a dark but lighted two-lane, two-way road with a -6% grade that was wet from rain. V2 pulled over to the right to attempt a U-turn. V1 proceeded to go around V2 on the left. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 deflected off the side of the road and impacted a curb and traveled roughly 21 m and impacted a small shrub and a large brick building with it's front plane.

V1 was traveling soutbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the west side of the roadway after avoiding a collision with a deer. Upon departing the roadway V1 struck a utility pole with the right side. V1 then overturned four quarter turns, left side leading. During the roll sequence the top of V1 struck a mailbox post causing a counterclockwise rotation during the roll sequence. V1 came to final rest on its wheels off the west side of the roadway facing east.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway.  V2 was traveling west on a one way alley attempting a left hand turn to access the roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound on a five lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on the intersecting five lane two way roadway, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue est. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was exiting a parking lot heading west attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling north in lane 2 of the intersecting five lane with continuous left turn lane roadway. V1 and V2 continued across multiple lanes to the left and came to final rest on the shoulder facing north. A fire started on the inside of V1 near the driver side B Pillar area.

Vehicle 1 was proceeding north through a 4 leg intersection after being stopped at a stop sign on a two way unmarked roadway. Vehicle 2 was headed east  on a two way roadway through the same intersection. Vehicle 1 struck vehicle 2's right side plane with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 came to final rest at the point of impact. Vehicle 2 went into a clockwise yaw following the impact and rolled 4 quarter turns coming to rest on the north side of the westbound lane on its wheels.

V2 was southbound on a two lane, two way highway. V1 was also southbound on the same highway behind V2. The front of V1 struck the back of V2. V1 then left the roadway to the right and struck a ditch before overturning four quarter turns to the left.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 had traveled westbound on the same roadway, made a left hand turn into a driveway and was backing up into the roadway from the driveway. The front end of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a divided roadway with four lanes.  Vehicle #2 was traveling west on the same roadway, attempting to turn left to continue south.  The front of V2 contacted the front of V1.

Vehicle 1, heading westbound, and Vehicle 2, heading eastbound, were approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1 attempted to make and left hand turn to head south. Vehicle 2 upon impact rotated slightly to the right and came to final rest at the southeast corner of the intersection facing east.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane 2 of a five lane undivided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling west on the intersecting two lane undivided roadway, attempting a right hand turn to continue north. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.

V1 was traveling north negotiating a curve in the number 2 lane of four lane limited access roadway composed of two lanes of northbound traffic and two lanes of southbound traffic separated by a dirt/grass median.
