V1 came to rest on its wheels facing northeast in the number 2 southbound lane. The front of V2 struck the left side of V1. The collision with V2 caused V1 to move south in the number 2 southbound lane where it came to final rest facing north. V2 continued to travel south after colliding with V1 coming to final rest on the west shoulder of the roadway. A subsequent crash was not reflected on the CISS selected PCR, but it involved a vehicle striking the front of V1 as it was blacked out (obscured by dust/no exterior or interior lighting) at final rest from the CISS crash in the the number one southbound lane of the roadway. This subsequent collision to V1 caused extensive overlapping damage to the exterior and interior of V1.

V1 was stopped on a 3 lane two way roadway in lane 2 going west. V1 was pulling a trailer. V2 was headed west in the same lane. V2 struck the rear plane of the trailer being towed by V1 with its front plane. The trailer of V1 caused damage to the rear plane of V1. V1 departed the right side of the roadway, striking a guardrail with its front plane. V1 then proceeded through the guardrail causing damage to the left side plane before coming to final rest north of the guardrail headed north. After striking the trailer of V1, V2 also departed the right side of the roadway striking the guardrail. V2 continued a northwest trajectory through the guardrail striking an embankment and coming to final rest north of the guardrail against the embankment.
V1 was traveling south, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the road to the right and the front end of V1 contacted a tree.

V1 was traveling west in the second lane of a four lane two-way undivided roadway. The driver of V1 attempted to avoid an animal in the road and departed the roadway at right. V1's front contacted an unfixed concrete curbing. V1's frontal plane then contacted the embankment at a slope and rotated counter clockwise. V1 then overturned onto it's left side. V1 came to final rest facing east in the first lane upright.

V1 was southbound on two-lane roadway. V2 was westbound the intersecting two-lane roadway. V1 and V2 entered the same intersection. The front of V1 collided with the right side of V2 (event 1). V1 came to final rest at Point of Impact. V2 came to final rest just west of point of impact.

V1 was traveling southbound on a one lane, one way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a three lane one way roadway in lane two approaching the same intersection. The front of V2 impacted a traffic sign pole, then V2 rolled over right side leading three quarter turns.
Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on a two way roadway. Vehicle 1 was exiting a parking lot. Vehicle 1's frontal plane struck Vehicle 2's right side plane.

V1 and V2 were going opposite directions on an undivided roadway. Vehicle #2 turned left, and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.. After the initial impact, V1 entered a counter clockwise yaw, departed the road and rolled one quarter turn onto the right side. During the roll, the top of V1 contacted three utility pole guy wires before coming to rest.
V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane non-divided roadway when it left the right side of the roadway and struck a tree with the right side plane, and then struck another tree with the front plane.

V1 was in lane two traveling north on a two lane one way roadway.  V1 departed the roadway on the left, traveling down an embankment until the front made contact with the ground and coming to final rest.
V1 was traveling north while exiting a private drive. V2 was headed west in lane one of a two lane undivided roadway. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2.
V2 was traveling north in lane 1 of a 2 lane with grass median roadway.  V1 was traveling behind V2 in the same travel lane when the front end of V1 contacted the rear end of V2.

V1 was traveling north in lane three of a five lane undivided roadway and was in the left turn lane negotiating a left turn to continue west. V2 was headed south in lane three of the same roadway. V1's front end struck the front end of V2 in the intersection where both vehicles came to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a gravel, two way roadway.  V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise, departing the roadway to the right.  The vehicle came to final rest when the left side of V1 made contact with a tree.

V1 was traveling northbound on 4 lane roadway. V1 made a right turn into a private parking lot. V1 continued through the parking lot and impacted with the undercarriage to train tracks (event 1). V1 came to final rest on the train tracks.

V1 was southbound on a 2 lane roadway. Deer entered roadway from the east.  The front of V1 collided with deer.  V1 then crossed northbound travel lane and came to final rest on the northbound travel lane shoulder.
V1 was traveling down a two lane two way undivided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted a deer in the travel lane and came to rest on the shoulder.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane non divided highway. A deer ran in front of V1 and was struck by the front  of V1. V1 then departed the roadway to the right and struck a barbed-wire-fence with the front plane and came to rest.

V1 was traveling south on a divided highway. V2 had been eastbound on the intersecting two lane undivided roadway, just completing a right hand turn.  V1 departed the left side of the road and continued through a ditch. V1 re-entered the road, traveling to the right across both southbound lanes where the front plane of V1 collided with the left plane of V2. V1 spun clockwise, causing V1 to roll left 4 quarter turns and landing on its wheels.

Vehicle 1 was stopped at an intersection preparing to make a right hand turn on to an undivided 4 lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the 4 lane roadway in lane 2 changing lanes to lane 1. Vehicle 1 initiated the turn and the front of Vehicle 2 collided into the left side of Vehicle 1.

V1 was traveling south on the connection ramp of two major highways. V1 was negotiating a right curve. Driver lost directional control of vehicle. V1 started to rotate clockwise and departed the roadway to the right. The left side of V1 impacted the concrete bridge pillar of an overpass.
V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a 5 lane major highway in lane 2. V2 was stalled in the lane ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, median divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east, on the same two way, median divided roadway as V1, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left. V1 turned left, departed the roadway to the south and hit a low wall with its front, coming to rest at the wall. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V2 was traveling west in the first lane on a five lane non physically divided roadway. V1 was traveling east in the second lane. V1 traveled into the third lane. V1 turned left, through fourth lane, over lane line, into fifth lane. The front of V2 impacted with the right side of V1.  Impact caused V1 and V2  to rotate counter clockwise.  V1 came to final rest facing north in fifth lane. V2 came to final rest facing west in original lane.
V1 and V2 were on an entrance ramp to merge onto a westbound interstate. The front of V1 collided with the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest at the point of impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on an entrance ramp to an interstate.  V1 departed lane to the left and then returned to the right. The right front side of V1 impacted with the left rear side of V2. V2 then departed lane and roadway to the right and impacted the right front side with the guardrail face, rotated counter clockwise where it came to final rest. V1 traveled to the left, leaving original lane and roadway. V1 then traveled through median before returning to roadway to the left and into the second and third lane. V1 then traveled out of lane to the left and impacted the front of vehicle with a jersey barrier. V1 rotated clockwise impacting the left side with the Jersey barrier. V1 came to a final rest facing west in the left shoulder.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two way non-physically divided traffic way separated by a left turn lane, attempting  to make a left turn. V2 was traveling westbound on the same traffic way in lane 1.  V1's right side made contact with the front of V2.

V1 was traveling west crossing over an intersection. V2 was traveling north passing through the same intersection. V1's right plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 and V2 then side slapped with V1's right plane contacting V2's left plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise and tripped and rolled right two quarter turns coming to rest on its top.
V1 and V2 were traveling northbound with V1 ahead of V2. V1's rear plane was contacted by V2's front plane. V1 left the scene of the crash.
V1 was north bound on a two lane roadway when a deer entered its path. V1's frontal plane impacted the animal.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane one way roadway. A deer ran in front of vehicle 1 and vehicle one struck the deer with its frontal plane causing damage to the front plane and continuing down the left side plane.
Both V1 and V2 were traveling southbound on a 3 lane with a coninuous left turn lane roadway in the #1 lane. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling southeast in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane interstate. V3 was stopped in traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The force of the impact forced V2 forward, where the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3.
V1, V2, and V3 were traveling eastbound in the #1 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2 pushing V2 forward, the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 causing V1 to rotate counter-clockwise. Both vehicles remained on the roadway at final rest.

V1 was traveling east in the second lane of a three lane two-way undivided roadway towards an intersection. V2 was traveling west in the second lane of a three lane two-way undivided roadway towards the same intersection. V1 turned left to head north and the front of V2 came in contact with the right side of V1.

V2 was traveling in the first lane of a two lane roadway heading southbound. An unknown vehicle (V1) was traveling eastbound in the first lane of the intersecting two lane roadway. The unknown vehicle's frontal plane contacted the right side plane of V2. V2 stayed in the first lane at final rest facing southbound.

Vehicle #1 was turning left at a intersection to travel east bound. Vehicle #2 was traveling west bound. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front bumper of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was northbound on a one way unmarked roadway, attempting to make a left turn. V1 departed the roadway to the left, traveled through a parking space, over a concrete parking stop, and down a hill coming to final rest facing south west.

V1 was heading northbound on a four lane two way roadway attempting to turn left to continue west. V2 was heading southbound on a four lane highway. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection.
V1 and V2 were traveling north on a four lane, two way positively divided roadway.  V2 was disabled in the first northbound lane.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a three lane two way roadway, attempting a left hand turn to continue north. V2 was traveling westbound on the same three lane two way roadway. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west bound in lane one. Vehicle #2 was traveling north bound on the intersecting roadway in lane two. V1's front end struck the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling east in lane 3 (left turn lane) attempting make a left hand turn to head south. V2 was traveling west in lane 2 and continued straight in the same intersection. V2's front end and V1's right side made contact in the intersection. Following the initial impact, V2 spun clockwise making frontal contact with V3 front end, who was stopped in lane 3 (left turn lane heading north but waiting to turn east) before coming to final rest.
V1 and V2 were traveling south on a 4 lane with median interstate roadway, V1 behind V2.  V1's front contacted V2's rear.
V1, V2 and V3 was north bound on a three lane, two way road. The front of V1 struck the rear of V2. The front V2 struck the rear of V3.
V1, V2 and V3 were all traveling west on a three lane with continuous left turn lane roadway. V1 struck the rear of V2, causing the front of V2 to strike the rear of V3.
V1 was traveling eastbound. V2 was exiting a driveway, attempting a right hand turn, traveling northbound to eastbound. The front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling west through an intersection. V2 was traveling south through the same intersection, while towing a trailer. In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the left side of the trailer towed by V2.

Vehicle # 1 was northbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  Vehicle # 2 was westbound in lane 1 on a three lane, two way roadway.  The front of Vehicle # 1 struck the left side of Vehicle # 2 in the intersection of the two roads.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a five lane divided roadway attempting to turn left to continue east. Vehicle 2 was northbound on the same roadway. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.
Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling north in lane one of a two northbound lane roadway. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling northwest.  V1 lost control and departed the road to the left.  V1 re-entered the road and the right of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V1 departed the road to the left again and rolled over.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue east. V2 was traveling northbound on the same roadway. The frontal plane of V2 made contact with the right plane of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a four lane divided roadway attempting to turn right to continue west. V1 departed the road to the left, impacted a concrete curb with the undercarriage plane and then entered a large, deep concrete ditch and sustained a front end impact to the bottom of the ditch.
V1 and V2 were traveling east bound on a four lane two way divided roadway, The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane roadway when it departed the roadway on the right side. The front of V1 contacted a utility pole and came to final rest off the roadway facing westbound.

V1 was traveling in the second lane of a four lane divided roadway heading eastbound. V2 was traveling in the first lane of the same roadway heading eastbound. V2 crossed left into the second lane. The driver's side view mirror of V2 impacted the right side plane of V1. V2 returned right its original lane, then departing the roadway right, its right side tire striking the curb.

V1 starting into a four legged intersection from a sign controlled two way roadway. V2 was in the intersection that V1 was entering. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway with traffic in opposite directions. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. While negotiating a right curve V1 crossed the double yellow center lines and entered the westbound lane of the roadway. The front of V1 collided with the front of V2.

V1 was eastbound on a divided highway. V2 and V3 were westbound on the same highway. V1 departed the left side (north) of the highway and impacted two shrubs (events 1 and 2) with its front. V1 continued northeast and entered the westbound lanes. The front of V1 struck the front of V2 (event 3). V2 began to roll over (event 4) when its undercarriage was impacted by the front of V3 (event 5).
Both Vehicle #1 and #2 were going northbound on the same roadway. Vehicle #2 was slowing for traffic ahead and was struck in the back plane by the frontal plane of Vehicle #1

V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane undivided roadway and was negotiating a curve when the vehicle departed the roadway on the right side to avoid striking a deer in the roadway. V1 then struck a tree with the frontal plane of the vehicle, which sheered off and struck the undercarriage of the vehicle. The vehicle then struck a second tree with the frontal plane and struck an embankment with the left rear undercarriage. The vehicle then began to rollover a quarter turn onto its left side and struck a warning sign with the top plane. The vehicle then rolled another quarter turn onto its top plane before coming to final rest.

V1 and V3 were traveling west on a 2 lane non-divided roadway, V2 was traveling east. V1 was negotiating a left hand curve when V1's front plane impacted V2's front plane. V3's front plane then impacted the back plane of V1.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane undivided roadway attempting to make a left hand turn to continue east.  V2 was traveling southbound on the intersecting  two lane undivided roadway. The left side of V1 was struck by the front of V2.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway, V2 was traveling east on the intersecting two lane undivided roadway. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling North on a two lane one way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two lane one way roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1 in the intersection. As a result of initial impact V1 rolled one quarter turn to the right.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southbound on the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the left in a counterclockwise rotation.  The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.  V2 then departed the roadway to the right where the front contacted a ditch and came to rest.  V1 came to rest in the middle of the road facing east.

V1 traveling south on a two lane one way roadway.  V1 departed the initial roadway left, striking the front on the ground and continued to travel a short distance where the front contacted a tree before coming to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west bound in lane one. Vehicle #2 was traveling south bound. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front bumper of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and contacted the left side on the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling east in lane in lane 2 of a 4 lane undivided roadway crossing through a 4 way intersection.  V2 was traveling west in lane 3 of a 4 lane undivided roadway negotiating a left turn through the same intersection.  The front end of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was headed east in lane 1 out of two lane private drive turning left to head north. V2 was headed north in lane three of a five lane divided roadway attempting to make a left turn into the driveway at the same intersection. Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided 3 lane roadway.Vehicle 2 was traveling west on an intersecting, 6 lane roadway. In the intersection, the right side of Vehicle 1 collided into the front side of Vehicle 2. Then, the right side of Vehicle 1 slapped into the left side of Vehicle 2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a roadway. V2 was traveling southbound on the same roadway. V1 began to turn left onto an intersecting roadway. The front V2 collided with the right of V1.

V1 was traveling westbound on a three lane roadway stopped in the #2 lane at an intersection.  V2 was traveling southbound on an eight lane divided roadway in the number 3 lane.  Both vehicles entered the intersection, with V1 turning left.  The frontal plane of V2 struck the right side of V1.
V1 was northbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 struck a deer with the frontal plane, coming to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the second lane of a four lane undivided two-way roadway attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling south in the first lane of a four lane undivided two-way roadway. V2 attempted to stop but lost traction on the snow and the front of V2 contacted the front of V1.

V2 and V1 were traveling in the northbound in lane two of a three-lane, two way road. V2 was stopped at a traffic signal when the front V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane non- physically divided roadway. V1 was traveling northbound negotiating a right curve on a three-lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southbound negotiating a left curve on the same roadway. V2 then crossed over the center line into the southbound lanes and the front of V2 contacted the front of V3.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a four lane, two way median divided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.
V1 was traveling east in the first lane on a two-lane, divided highway, approaching an exit ramp. The front of V1 impacted a traffic attenuator. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact.

V1 was exiting the interstate onto a state route. V1 departed the roadway to the left, its front impacting a concrete traffic barrier.  V1 rolled over 1 quarter turn to the right then the top plane of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane two on a two way divided roadway with four lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling in the same direction and on the same roadway in front of V1. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2.

V1 was northbound on a 3-lane divided highway with a depressed median. V1 left the roadway to the right side into a depressed ditchline. V1 continued up an embankment rolling an additional 5-quarter turns coming to rest on its top on a side road.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway. Vehicle 1 and 2 were crossing through a four way intersection.  The front of Vehicle 2 contacted the right side of Vehicle 1.

V1 was traveling north in the #1 lane on a divided roadway with 2 northbound lanes. V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway. V1 lost control and departed the roadway to the right and impacted an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.
Both Vehicles #1 and #2 were going southbound on a four lane undivided roadway. Vehicle #1 struck the back plane of Vehicle #2 with its frontal plane.

V1 was heading south on a two way driveway, entering a crossover to turn left and travel east on the divided roadway. V2 was traveling west on a one lane divided roadway.  At the intersection, V1's front plane struck the right side plane of Vehicle 2.

V1 was traveling south in the number one lane on a three lane divided highway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway. The front of V1 struck a mile marker post (event 1). V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side impacting a curb with the frontal plane. V1 then impacted a fire hydrant with the frontal plane, where it came to final rest.

V2 was traveling north on a divided roadway with 3 northbound lanes, in the #1 lane.  V1 was exiting a private drive/parking lot are, attempting to make a right hand turn to continue north. V1 was traveling westbound on a curved divided highway with a grass median. V1 departed the roadway to the right (north) and continued off the roadway. The front of V1 contacted an embankment (event 1). V1 continued on the grass roadside and rolled four quarter turns.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way roadway.  V1 swerved to avoid a deer that was entering the roadway from the south.  V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted a tree stump.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane two way roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. The left side of V1 then contacted the same deer in the roadway.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way highway. The front of V1 struck a deer in the road.

V1  was traveling southbound on a two lane undivided roadway, attempting a left hand turn to continue east. V2 was traveling west in lane #1 of a divided roadway with three lanes westbound. The front of V2 collided with the left side of V1's utility trailer.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two-lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was parked in a private driveway facing east.  Vehicle 1 departed the right road edge and contacted a newspaper box post.  Vehicle # 1 continued south and contacted the front end of Vehicle 2 with its right side.  Vehicle 1 returned to the roadway and contacted a parked utility trailer.  Vehicle 1 continued southbound, crossed both lanes and departed the left road edge. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted a metal mailbox and continued to travel southwest into a yard.  Vehicle 1 contacted a tree and came to rest.

V1 was traveling east on the Interstate in lane 2, and was overtaking V2. V2 was traveling in lane 1 and was approaching V3. V3 was parked on the right shoulder. V1 and V2 were traveling west on the Interstate in lane 4, with V1 directly behind V2. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V2 departed the road on the left and struck a concrete barrier. V1 overturned on the roadway (2 quarter turns, leading right).

Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the east roadway. The left front wheel of V1 contacted a culvert which initiated a counter clockwise yaw. V1 was traveling north in the number two lane of a four lane limited access roadway composed of two lanes of northbound traffic and two-lanes of southbound traffic separated by a dirt/grass median without a positive barrier. V1 traveled across the northbound lanes and departed the right side of the roadway and onto a dirt/grass embankment. Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 4 lane roadway and attempting to make a left turn at an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on the same roadway. Vehicle 2's frontal plane struck the right side plane of Vehicle 1.

V1 was traveling in lane four of a two-way physically divided roadway with four lanes of travel westbound and two lanes of travel eastbound. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the right side plane of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound exiting a parking lot, attempting a right hand turn to continue east. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 impacted a utility pole then the front right tire impacted a curb.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway.  V1 departed its original travel lane to the left, then departed the roadway to the left and impacted a pole with its front.

Vehicle 1 was northbound in the third of three lanes pulling a trailer. Vehicle 2 was northbound in the same lane behind V1. V1 began to change lanes to the right and the front of V2 contacted the back of V1's trailer.

Vehicle 1 was westbound , entering the roadway from a 3 lane drive, attempting to make a left to continue south.  Vehicle 2 was northbound on the intersecting five lane with continuous left turn lane roadway. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 was traveling south on a two way not physically divided roadway, V2 was traveling south bound on same roadway attempting to turn right at a three legged intersection.  The front of V1 contacted the right rear side of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane two of a five lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound on the intersecting three lane undivided roadway, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue south. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2, both vehicles coming to final rest within the intersection.

V1 was north bound in lane one of a two way undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left where it first struck a tree with its left side and then shortly after struck another tree with its front end where it came to final rest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast on a two lane roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling southwest on the intersecting three lane one way roadway, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning left; V2 entered the intersection going straight, and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest in the crossover, facing south and V2 came to rest on the north shoulder west of the intersection.

All vehicles were traveling westbound in lane one, of an interstate roadway. V2 and V3 were traveling ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one, on a four lane divided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a wooden utility pole. V1 started to rotate clockwise. The left rear wheel impacted a raised curb. V1 continued to move southeast, traveling through a parking lot while rotating clockwise. The left side of V1 impacted a building. Debris from the building fell on top of V1.

Vehicle 1 (a medium heavy truck) was traveling west on a two way undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on the same roadway. Vehicle 2 struck the front plane of vehicle 1 with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 continued west, departed the roadway to the right, and tipped over on its right side, striking a tree, and coming to final rest heading west. Vehicle 2 continued east and came to rest heading southwest partially on its original travel lane and partially on the shoulder.

V1 was west bound on a two lane non divided residential street, approaching an intersection. V2 was south bound on a two lane non divided residential street, approaching the same intersection. As the both vehicle entered the intersection, V1's right plane impacted V2's frontal plane.

V1 was traveling north on an undivided roadway entering a light controlled four legged intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway entering the same intersection. V3 was stopped facing south at the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left of V2 (event 1). After the initial impact, V1 rotated counterclockwise and V2 rotated clockwise, causing the left side of V2 to contact the right side of V1 (event 2). V2 continued northbound, into the southbound lane of traffic, its front contacting the front of V3 (event 3). V2 and V3 came to final rest at impact. V1 continued southwest crossing the roadway before departing it to the left where the front of V1 impacted a building (event 4). V1 came to final rest after impact.

V1 was driving northbound on an icy roadway when V1 started to lose control.  V1 attempted to correct the yaw, but over corrected and departed the roadway on the right (east) side.  The right side of V1 impacted the guard rail on the east side of the roadway.  A climb over was initiated, and subsequent to traveling over the guardrail, V1 rolled 5 quarter turns, coming to final rest on the passenger side.
V1 was traveling South on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west on the intersecting two lane undivided roadway.  V1's front contacted V2's right side.
V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a two lane roadway undivided roadway. A non contact vehicle stopped in front of V2. V1's front contacted V2's rear.
V1 was backing up on a two lane undivided roadway in a northerly direction, and departed the roadway to the right. V1 backed into a chain link fence, before coming to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest on an undivided 4 lane roadway in lane 1. Vehicle departed the roadway on the north side of the road and the front of vehicle 1 struck 2 utility poles. (Both poles severed at their bases. Point of impact 2 was when Pole #1 struck the roof of vehicle 1 and point of impact 4 was when Pole #2 struck the top, right rear corner of vehicle 1.) Vehicle 1 continued in a southwesterly direction, meandering across the roadway, onto the southern sidewalk, back across the roadway and came to rest on the north side of the road approximately 722 meters southwest of the initial point of impact with the utility pole.
V1 and V2 were traveling east on a 2 lane not physically divided roadway, V1 behind V2.  The left side of V1 made contact with the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling westerly on a two way two lane undivided roadway.  V1 was negotiating a left curve with downward grade causing V1 to depart their original travel lane on the right hand side.  V1 completed four quarter turns before coming to rest on their wheels off of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were traveling north bound on an Interstate roadway, V1 in lane two, V2 to the right and slightly ahead in lane one. The front of V1 struck the back of V2's trailer. Subsequently, the left side of V1 incurred damage by an unknown event.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane two, on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway . V1 departed the roadway to the right at an end departure. V1 contacted the front bumper on two trees and then contacted the undercarriage on some rocks. V1 contacted the front bumper on two more trees and then rotated counter-clockwise and contacted the right side on another tree.

V2 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 was traveling east on the intersecting two lane undivided roadway. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 departed its original lane to the left, crossed the southbound lane and departed the roadway on the left, where it impacted a small tree with its front plane.
V1 and V2 were traveling north in lane two of a two-way, four-lane undivided roadway. V1 in front of V2. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 1-lane one way roadway, attempting to crossover an intersection.  V2 was traveling southbound on a 2-lane, 2-way undivided roadway, attempting to crossover the same intersection.  The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  V2 then departed the roadway in a southwest direction where the right side of V2 contacted an unknown diameter tree.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way road way. A deer crossed the roadway striking the front end of V1. V1 came to final rest on the right side shoulder.
V1 and V2 were southbound on a two way, two lane roadway. V2 was slowing for traffic ahead. The front of V2 collided with the rear of V1. V1 and V2 came to final rest at point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was southbound in the first of three lanes. Vehicle 2 was southbound in the same lane behind V1. Vehicle 3 was southbound in the same lane behind V2. Vehicle 4 was southbound in the same lane ahead of V1. V4 slowed for traffic and the front of V1 contacted the back of V4. The front of V2 then contacted the back of V1. The front of V3 then contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was west in the first lane of a divided roadway with three westbound lanes. Vehicle 2 was traveling in the same lane ahead of V1. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and returned to the roadway over the same side. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2, causing both V1 and V2 to rotate counter-clockwise, crossing all lanes of traffic to the left side. V2 departed the roadway to the left, its front contacting the concrete barrier, where it came to final rest. The front of V1 then contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the third lane of a six lane divided roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the right, traveled over two travel lanes on the right, and departed the roadway on the right side.  V1 impacted a guardrail with its frontal plane. V1 rotated counter-clockwise impacting the rear plane into the guardrail. V1 then returned to the first lane in the roadway at final rest, facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two-lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side. V1 overrode a flush curb adjacent to a sidewalk and  continued to travel southerly, impacting a handicap sign with the frontal plane. V1 came to final rest facing southbound.

V1 was westbound entering a five lane road from a business parking lot attempting to turn left to continue south. V2 was eastbound entering the same road from a business attempting to turn let to continue north. The front of V1 struck the front of V2. Point of impact was in the center turn lane.

Vehicle 1 was west bound on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was northbound in lane one of a five lane, two way roadway.  The front of Vehicle 1 struck the right side of Vehicle 2.
V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way roadway. The front of V1 struck a deer.

Vehicle # 1 was traveling east and vehicle # 2 was going traveling south on an intersecting roadway. Vehicle #1 began to turn left at the intersection, and the front of vehicle # 2 struck the left plane of vehicle # 1.

Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 (motorcycle) were traveling West on an undivided two lane roadway. The front plane of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 continued down the road before departing the roadway to the left. The front plane of V1 contacted a small wooden post, then a tree.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane 1 of a six lane two way roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in lane 3 of the intersecting three lane two way roadway, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue north. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. The left side of V2 then contacted the right side of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a four lane, two way roadway.  V2 was traveling eastbound on the intersecting one lane, one way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.  The left side of V1 then contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was heading northbound on a four lane two way roadway with a grass median approaching the same intersection. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection.
V1 was traveling west on an Interstate roadway in lane 2 when it departed the roadway on the left and overturned (leading left, 8 quarter turns).

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane undivided roadway, through the right hand curve of an "S" turn when it departed its lane to the left, then roadway on the left. The front end of V1 contacted a tree, and V1 caught fire.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 on a three lane undivided roadway, attempting to make a U-turn.  V2 was traveling on the same roadway to the left of V1 in lane 2.  The front end of V2 came into contact with the left side of V1.
Vehicles #1 and #2 were stopped facing north in lane 4 of a divided roadway with 5 northbound lanes.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a four lane undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling south on the same roadway, attempting to make a left hand turn into a parking lot. The front of V1 contacted the right of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction attempting to turn left at the intersection.  V2 was traveling eastbound also on a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction with a left turn lane.  At the intersection of the above roadways, the frontal plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1.  After the impact, V1 departed roadway on the right side and the right front wheel made contact with the curb. V2 also departed the roadway on the right side and its right front wheel made contact with the curb.

V1 was westbound in the #7 (HOV) lane.  V1 departed its lane to the right, crossing over 6 travel lanes, departing the roadway to the right, its front end striking the concrete barrier wall. V1 spun clockwise after initial impact maintaining contact with barrier, then made a second contact with concrete barrier to its left side before completing a full spin and coming to rest back on the roadway, in the  #1 and #2 lanes.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway, attempting to make a left hand to turn to continue north. V1 departed the roadway on the right side, its front end striking a curb, and then a concrete wall.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane roadway with traffic in opposite directions. As V1 entered a T-intersection of the roadway and the northern terminus of a two lane north/south roadway with traffic in opposite directions, V1 departed the right side of the roadway at the southeast corner of the intersection. V1 continued to travel off the roadway and the front of V1 struck a traffic signal control box. V1 came to final rest at the point of the collision with the control box.
V1 was east bound on a four lane roadway divided by a grass median. The front of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the south side of the roadway facing east.

V1 was heading south on a two lane two-way undivided roadway, attempting to turn left to continue east. V2 was heading west on the intersecting two lane two-way undivided roadway. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was legally parked in the northbound lane, facing north. V1 departed its lane of travel to the left, crossed over the northbound lane, departed the roadway to the left, the left side of V1 colliding with the left side of V2. V1 continued to travel forward crossing both the northbound and southbound lanes and traveling off the right side of the roadway. As V1 traveled off the roadway the front  impacted a raised cement curb. V1 continued to travel off the roadway on to a sidewalk and the front of V1 struck a concrete wall. V1 came to final rest facing southwest straddling the sidewalk with its front against the concrete wall.

V1 was traveling north on a four-lane interstate in lane three. V1 crossed the lane line on the right and the front right tire impacted a curb. The vehicle then departed the roadway on the right hand side. V1 traveled down an embankment where the right side impacted a tree. The vehicle then rotated counter clockwise around the tree and rolled over on its left side, where it came to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway going into the ditch and up an embankment. V1 then veered left towards the roadway, impacting the ditch with the left frontal plane, causing the vehicles rear end to rotate counterclockwise along the embankment, rolling over 1 quarter turn before coming to final rest on its right side in the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was going north on a three lane undivided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling west on the intersecting two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1's front struck the left side of Vehicle 2. After the initial impact, both vehicles rotated resulting in the right side of Vehicle #1 striking the left side of Vehicle #2 before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane roadway approaching a right-hand curve. V1 departed its lane on the left side, returned on the left side where it entered a clockwise rotation before departing the roadway on the right side. After departing the roadway the left side of V1 struck a large tree and the front struck a small tree before coming to final rest.

V2 was traveling west on a two lane two way roadway. V1 was traveling eastbound on same roadway. V1 left it's original travel lane, crossed over the left lane. The front of V2 contacted the front of V1. After the initial impact, V1 began to rotate counterclockwise, its rear plane striking the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling north towards an intersection on a 6 lane divided roadway, V2 was traveling south towards the same intesection. V1 entered the left turn lane and turned left at the traffic signal. The frontal plane of V2 impacted the frontal plane of V1.
V1 was traveling west on a 2 lane undivided roadway attempting to overtake a truck when it departed the road to the left.  After departing the roadway, V1's front end struck a utility pole.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a three lane divided roadway attempting to make a left hand turn to continue north. V2 was traveling north in lane two of the intersecting four lane divided roadway. V1's right side was struck by the front of V2. Both vehicles then departed the roadway to the right, the northeast apex of the intersection where V1 contacted a utility pole with its front end.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway when it departed the roadway to the right where it contacted a culvert with its undercarriage.  The initial impact caused V1 to overturn 2 quarter turns to the right, where it contacted a utility locator box with an unknown plane before coming to a final rest on its top.

V1 traveling south on two lane interstate highway, with two southbound lanes. V1 began to rotate clockwise and went off the right side of the road with the left side leading. V1 rolled 6 quarter turns coming to final rest on the top plane.

V1 was north bound on a two lane non divided roadway, negotiating a left hand curve. V1 left the roadway to the right, where it impacted a guardrail with its frontal plane. V1 then rolled onto its left side where it came to final rest.
V1 and V2 were traveling south in lane 1 of a 2 lane divided roadway.  V1's front plane struck the back plane of V2.
V1 was traveling east in the number 1 lane on a 5 lane non-divided road when a deer ran in front of V1 from the right shoulder. The deer was struck with the front left corner of V1.
All vehicles were traveling east on an interstate roadway, entering the exit ramp from the highway.  The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 was pushed forward and impacted V3 with its front.

V1 was traveling north on a divided 4 lane roadway in lane 4, attempting a left hand turn to continue west into a driveway. V2 was traveling south on the same divided roadway in lane 1. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.
V1 was traveling south on a four-lane roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped in the same travel lane as V1 prior to the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane one way roadway in lane 2. An  unknown vehicle from lane 1 began turning into Vehicle 1's lane and vehicle 1 turned onto the north shoulder and struck a guardrail end with its left side plane. Vehicle 1 then came to final rest on the north side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a three lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on the intersecting three lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 struck the left side plane of vehicle 2 with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 came to final rest in the intersection headed north east. Vehicle 2 came to final rest in the intersection headed north.
V1 was southbound  in lane 2 on a 4 lane roadway.  V2 was northbound in lane 2 on the same 4 lane roadway.  V2 entered the oncoming travel lane.  The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was eastbound on an two lane roadway without a positive barrier. V1 departed its initial travel lane then the roadway to the left. V1 rolled 4 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its wheels.

V1 and V2 were traveling southbound on a two-lane, two-way, undivided roadway.  The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2 while V2 was stopped for a deer that was in the roadway.  V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway entering a sign controlled four-legged intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway entering the same intersection as V1. In the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2

V1 was northbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was southbound on same roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted with the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the same approximate location as impact.

V1 was traveling southwest on an unmarked roadway preparing to make a left turn to continue east. V2 was northbound on the three lane undivided intersecting roadway. V3 was parked facing south, on the intersecting roadway. The front of V2 impacted with the left of V1 (event 1). V1 begun rotating counter clockwise, the left side of V1 to impacting with V2's left side (event 2). V1  then continued rotating counter clockwise, departing the roadway to the right, the right of V1 impacted with the left of V3 (event 3). V1 came to final rest facing southeast. V2 came to final rest facing north. V3's final rest at location of impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound on a 3 lane undivided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane one on the intersecting divided roadway with 1 left turn lane and 2 northbound lanes. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling east on a 4 lane non-physically divided roadway attempting to make a left hand turn.  V2 was traveling westbound on the same roadway.  The front of V2 struck the right side of V1.
V1 was southbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 struck a deer with the frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the west side of the roadway facing south.

V1 was east bound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 crossed over the left lane and continued off the roadway to the left (north). V1 initiated a counter-clockwise rotation while traveling down a ditch. Upon contact with the bottom of the ditch V1 initiated a right side roll. V1 Rolled 2 quarter turns into the north side of the ditch with the top plane. Upon contact with the north ditch wall V1 was catapulted into an end over end roll 1 quarter turn to land on the right front tire. At the moment of the right front tire contact V1 then continued with the front end facing downwards towards the east catching the right front again while spinning counter-clockwise. The front plane of V1 struck the ground again while continuing its counter clockwise spin. V1 then rolled 1 quarter turn onto the left side before rolling 1 quarter turn onto the top before coming to final rest at the bottom of the ditch facing west.

V1 was in the first lane of a divided roadway with two southbound lanes. A deer ran into the roadway. The deer was struck by the frontal plane of V1. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway facing southbound.

V1 was traveling west in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V1 attempted to avoid a deer in the road and departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted a utility pole.

V1 was traveling northwest attempting to make a left turn at an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast attempting to pass through the same intersection. V1's right plane was contacted by V2's front plane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on an undivided 5 lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on an intersecting, undivided 2 lane roadway. Both vehicles entered into the intersection and the front of Vehicle 2 collided into the right side of Vehicle 1.
V1 was traveling westbound on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway.  V2 was stopped ahead of V1 on the same roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a six lane two way median divided roadway, attempting a left hand turn to continue west. V2 was traveling southbound on the same six lane two way median divided roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection.
V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  V2 was stopped ahead of V1 on the same roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were traveling south. V2 slowed for traffic and the front plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. V1 then overturned two quarter turns onto its roof and departed the roadway on the right (west) side.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast in lane 1 of a divided roadway with two lanes. Vehicle #2 was traveling in lane 2, to the left of V1 on the same roadway. The left plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V2 began rotating clockwise, departed its lane to the right, crossed lane one and departed the road to the right. The left plane of V1 contacted a tree.
Vehicle #1 and vehicle #2 were traveling south in lane two of a four lane divided roadway, V1 behind V2. The front end of V1 struck the back end of V2.
Vehicle 1 was eastbound in the first of four lanes approaching an exit. V1 departed the roadway to the left side and the front of V1 contacted a impact attenuator.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in the first lane of a divided roadway with two southbound  lanes. V1 departed the roadway to the right, striking the curb, then proceeding to strike a brick barrier wall with its front end.
V1 was traveling south on the Interstate in lane 1 when it departed the roadway on the right and came into contact with a ditch/culvert and a fence.
V1 and V2 were traveling south on the Interstate in lane 4, with V1 directly behind V2. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound negotiating the left hand curve in lane 2 of a two way, four lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the right, then the roadway on the right. V1 rotated counterclockwise and skidded laterally in an open dirt area.  V1's right side came into contact with a building and a wall, simultaneously.  V1 then rotated clockwise and overturned (4 quarter turns, leading left).  V1's rollover was interrupted when its left side came into contact with a storage container.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south on an exit ramp, attempting to turn right to continue west.  Vehicle #2 was traveling west on an intersecting divided with 4 westbound lanes roadway.  The left of V1 contacted the front of V2. After the initial contact, V1 began to rotate clockwise, its left side striking the right side of V2.

V1 was westbound on a one lane ramp, departed the roadway to the left, where it struck an impact attenuator- concrete barrier with an unknown vehicle plane. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise, and began to overturn an unknown amount of quarter turns, crossing the travel lane to the right, departing the roadway to the right, coming  to rest on the north side of the roadway facing east.

V1 was heading north on a two lane roadway, attempting a left hand turn to continue west. V2 was traveling east in lane two, of the intersecting 5 lane with continuous left turn lane roadway. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling northbound on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane on the left side and the frontal plane of V1 made impact with the frontal plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was northbound in lane two of a five lane, undivided two way roadway.  Vehicle 2 was westbound in lane two of the intersecting three lane, undivided two way roadway, turning left to continue south. The front of Vehicle 1 collided with the left side of Vehicle 2.

V1 was north bound on a two lane, two way snow covered highway. V1 lost control on the icy road. The driver of V1 attempted to steer out of the skid, and rotated clockwise. V1 traveled into a depressed ditch line and continued to roll left. The right side of the pickup bed contacted a tree that interrupted the roll. V1 settled back and remained on its left side.

V1 was east bound on a non divided two lane roadway, when it left the roadway to the right. V1 impacted two trees with its right plane. It then impacted two trees with its frontal plan before coming to final rest.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane snow covered roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane struck a road sign and a tree stump.
V1 was traveling westbound  on a four lane undivided roadway. V2 was legally parked against the curb facing north. V1 departed the roadway to the right,its front contacting V2's rear.

Vehicle 1 was westbound in the fifth of a five lane interstate roadway. Vehicle 2, 3, 4 and 5 were westbound in the first lane of the same roadway. V1 departed it's original lane to the right, crossed through all other lanes and departed the roadway on the right side. The front of V1 struck a light pole. The pole fell into the travel lanes. The undercarriage of V2 contacted the pole. Then the undercarriage of V3 contacted the pole. Then the undercarriage of V4 contacted the pole. Lastly, the front of V5 contacted the pole.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, divided one way highway in lane one. V2 was entering the highway from and intersecting two lane roadway intending to head north. In the north bound lane the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. After the initial impact, V1 rotated in a clockwise yaw and rolled two quarter turns coming to rest on its roof. V2 came to rest on the east shoulder of the roadway.
V1 was traveling northbound when it departed the roadway on the right side. After departing the roadway V1 struck three wooden posts with the front plane.

V1 was traveling westbound on a four-lane roadway attempting to make a left turn and head northbound. While making the left turn, V1 lost control and entered a counterclockwise yaw. V1 departed the roadway on the left side where it struck a curb (Event 1) and three sign-posts (Events 2, 3 & 4) V1 continued westbound where it crossed another roadway and struck a utility pole with its right side plane (Event 5).

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a five lane with continuous left turn lane roadway. Vehicle 1 departed its lane to the left, crossed over the northbound lanes and departed the roadway to the left, traveling into a grassy area. Vehicle 1's frontal plane struck a brick wall.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a three lane undivided roadway entering an intersection. V2 was traveling south, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue east. V1's frontal plane struck the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling in front of V2 as both vehicles traveled north in lane one of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V2's front end struck the back of V1.

V1 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane divided roadway. While passing through the intersection an unknown vehicle also entered the intersection and encroached into V1's travel lane. V1 departed the roadway to the left where it struck the curb and then a sign with the front end of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling North in lane 3 of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west in lane one of a 2 way undivided roadway, attempting a right hand turn to continue north. The front end of V2 contacted the right side of V1 before coming to a final rest in the roadway.
V1, V2, and V3 were traveling west on a two lane, undivided roadway. V1 impacted the back of V2 with its front plane. As a result the front of V2 impacted the back of V3.
V1 was traveling south on a divided interstate roadway with two southbound lanes. A deer entered the roadway and was struck by the front end of V1.  V1 came to final rest on the shoulder.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 of a 2 lane divided roadway when the vehicle departed the left side of the roadway. The vehicle  then returned to the roadway and departed the right side of the roadway where it struck an embankment. It then traveled up and across the embankment, and as the vehicle began to travel back down the embankment, it rotated in a counter clockwise direction. The vehicle then proceeded to rollover over 6 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its top.

V1 was traveling north on a divided 2 lane freeway in the number two lane. V1 departed the roadway to the left, striking a cable guardrail post with the front of V1. V1's left side the struck the cable barrier before coming to rest on the left-side shoulder.
V1 was traveling west on a  two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 impacted a pair of utility poles with its front.
V1 was traveling on a four lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left, the front of V1 impacting a light pole located on the median.

V1 was traveling southbound on a four lane undivided roadway in lane 2, attempting to make a left hand turn into a private drive. V2 was traveling northbound on the same roadway in lane 2. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling North in lane 1 of a 4 lane divided highway. V2 was traveling West on the intersecting undivided roadway. The front of V1 collided with the left plane of V2. V1 came to final rest in the intersection. V2 entered a clockwise yaw and the left plane of V2 collided with the right plane of V1, before coming to final rest facing East.

V1 was northbound on a two lane non divided roadway.V1 left the roadway to the right, where it impacted an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then impacted a tree and an culvert with its frontal plane.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway.  V2 was traveling west, attempting to make a right hand turn from a driveway to continue north.The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2 who was towing a trailer.  V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was northbound on a two-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was southbound on the same roadway approaching the intersection. V1 began to make a left turn to travel west. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane 2 of a 3 lane undivided roadway, attempting a left hand turn to continue south.  V2 was traveling north in lane 2 of  the intersecting divided roadway with 4 northbound lanes.  The front of V1 struck the right side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the right side of the roadway, came back onto the roadway, departed its lane and then the roadway to the left striking a fence with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 came to rest on the south side of the fence that runs parallel to the roadway.
Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling south on an undivided 2 lane roadway. The front of Vehicle 1 collided with the rear of Vehicle 2.

V1 and V2 were both southbound on a four-lane highway. V1 was in lane four and V2 was in lane three. V1 merged into lane three. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2 (event 1). Subsequently, V2 departed the left side (east) of the road and its front impacted a concrete barrier (event 2).

V1 was traveling southwest on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front undercarriage contacted the ground. V1 went into a counter clockwise rotation and tripped and rolled right six quarter turns coming to final rest on the top.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway, attempting a left turn to continue south. V2 was traveling north on the intersecting divided roadway with two northbound lanes of traffic. V1's left plane was contacted by V2's front plane. After the collision V2 rotated counter clockwise and departed its travel lanes and the roadway to the left. V2 tripped and rolled right two quarter turns, coming to final rest on its roof in the median.

V2 was heading south at an intersection in lane one of two of a divided two-way road. V1 was traveling west in lane one on the intersecting three lane divided two-way road. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 causing V2 to rotate counter-clockwise.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided 2 lane street. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on an intersecting, undivided, 2 lane street. The front of Vehicle 1 collided into the left side of vehicle 2.

V1 was southbound on a two lane two way unmarked roadway. V1 came over a hill crest departing the right side of the roadway. V1 returned to the roadway in a counter-clockwise yaw. V1 departed the left side of the initial travel lane and continuing off the left side of the roadway striking an embankment with the front plane. Upon striking the embankment V1 continued the counter-clockwise rotation 180 degrees facing north and continuing south. V1 traveled 10m before rolling left side leading 1 quarter turn coming to final rest on the driver's side facing north.

V1 was westbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway traveling down an embankment into a tree line. V1 impacted a tree stump causing damage to the right plane. Continued at a north western trajectory impacting a tree with the frontal plane before coming to final rest at point of impact 2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in the first of  a divided roadway with four southbound lanes.  V1 departed the road on the right side where the front of V1 contacted a signal pole. A fire in the engine compartment of the vehicle then occurred.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a two-lane divided roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling in lane 2 on the same roadway.  V1  changed lanes to the left and the front of Vehicle 2 contacted the back of Vehicle 1.
V1 was traveling north in the #1 lane. V2 was stopped in the same #1 lane, also heading north. The front of V1 made contact with the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a four-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was southbound on a five-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two lane, two way roadway, V2 ahead of V1 approaching a light controlled four-legged intersection. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a three lane, two way roadway.  V2 was traveling eastbound on the intersecting three lane, two way roadway.  V3 was stopped facing southbound on a three lane, two way roadway at the intersection. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  V1 then departed the roadway to the left, the undercarriage contacting a planter. After impact with V1, V2 rotated counterclockwise, traveling into the southbound lane, its front contacting the front of V3.

V1 was traveling northbound on a five lane two way median divided roadway, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue west. V2 was traveling southbound on the same five lane two way median divided roadway. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a four lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in the second lane, to the left if V1. The left side plane of V1 impacted the right side plane of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling northbound on the intersecting two lane undivided roadway.  The left side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was heading west on a private driveway, attempting to make a right hand turn onto the roadway to continue north. V2 was heading northbound on a one way access road, in lane two. V2's front contacted V1's rear.
V1 and V2 were traveling northbound lane one of a four lane divided interstate with V1 traveling behind V2.  V1's front contacted V2's rear.

Vehicle 1 was southbound in lane one of a two lane roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane one on the intersecting divided roadway with two westbound lanes of a four lane roadway.  Vehicle 2's front end collided with Vehicle 1 left side.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway, when a deer crossed the road from the right. V1 departed the road to the left and the front plane contacted a barbed wire fence, then two trees.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north approaching the same intersection. V1 began to turn left. The front plane of V2 contacted the left front plane of V1. The left plane of V2 contacted a guardrail.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north approaching a four way intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling east on the intersecting roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the left of V1 contacted the front of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast in lane three of a three lane roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling northwest in lane one on the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 rotated clockwise and departed the road to the left.  The left of V1 contacted a pole and came to rest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound on a two lane unmarked roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and then re-entered the roadway from the right side. V1 departed the lane on the left side and departed the roadway on the left, its front plane striking a fence post.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way two lane roadway in the number 1 lane. V2 was traveling northeast on a 5 lane center turn lane divided roadway in the number 2 lane. V1 was attempting to turn left at a T type intersection. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. After impact V1 traveled off the road to the north and came to rest off partially on the sidewalk and partially in the grass. V2 came to rest in the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane 1 of a five lane center turn lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in lane 1 lane of the same roadway. V1 departed the road to the right with the the RF wheel impacting the curb. V1 returned to the roadway and crossed all lanes into westbound lanes. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling north in the number 1 lane of a limited access roadway composed of two lanes of northbound traffic and two lanes of southbound traffic separated by metal guardrail. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and the front of V1 struck a concrete drain pipe. After colliding with the drain pipe V1 overturned three quarter turns to the right about its longitudinal axis and continued to travel off road striking a tarp covered fence. V1 came to final rest off the roadway on its driver's side facing west.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane 3 of a 5 lane undivided roadway at an intersection attempting to turn left to travel north. V2 was traveling westbound in lane 1 of a 2 lane median divided roadway. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on the Interstate in lane 1.  V1 front/right came into contact with V2's back/left.  V1 overturned on the roadway (6 quarter turns, leading right) then departed the roadway on the right and continued to overturn (6 quarter turns, leading right).  V2 departed the roadway on the right and overturned (10 quarter turns, leading right), during which time it came into contact with a sign post.
V1 was traveling east on a five lane physically divided roadway in lane 4 when it departed the roadway on the left, and its front end contacted a guard rail face.

V1 was traveling west on the Interstate in lane 2 when it departed its lane and then the roadway on the right and came into contact with a guardrail. V1 returned to the roadway, crossing all lanes to the left then back to the right again, departing the roadway on the the right for a second time, overturning (6 quarter turns, leading left) and came into contact with a fence before final rest.

V1 was traveling westbound in the left lane of a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction attempting to turn left at the intersection heading southbound.  V2 was traveling eastbound in the right lane of the same roadway.  At the intersection of the above roadways, the frontal plane of V1 contacted the left side plane of V2.  This caused the RF wheel of V2 to contact the curb of the southeast corner.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west bound in lane two of a four lane undivided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling north bound entering the roadway from a private drive, to continue north. V1's front struck the right side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two way positively divided highway in lane one of three northbound lanes. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway in lane three. V1 departed the roadway to the right striking a guardrail with it's front plane. V1 re-entered the roadway in a clockwise rotation crossing all lanes to the left, and was struck on the right, rear side plane by V2's frontal plane.

V2 was stopped in lane 3 at a traffic light on the southbound side of a divided highway. V1 was traveling south in lane 2 on the same roadway, approaching the intersection from the same direction. The front plane of V1 impacted the back plane of V2.
V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane, two way, roadway when the vehicle departed the right side of the roadway and struck a tree with its front end.
V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a two-lane roadway. V1 was attempting a right turn into a business parking lot when the front of V2 contacted the rear of V1.

V1 was traveling westbound on a three-lane roadway when V1 departed the roadway on the right side. The front plane of V1 struck a guardrail and continued off the roadway where the front plane stuck a metal fence. V1 then traveled off a 40ft embankment where the front plane contacted the ground before rolling over onto its passenger side.

V1 was southbound on a two lane non divided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the right side. V1 attempted to avoid striking the animal, leaving the roadway to the right, where it impacted an embankment causing V1 to rollover five quarter turns, left side leading, coming to final rest on its left side.

V1 was traveling in a westerly direction in the number 3 on a two-way roadway with a continuous left hand turn lane and attempted a left turn into a private drive. V2 was traveling in a easterly direction in the number 2 lane approaching the same private drive. V1 right side made contact with V2 front. V1 rotated clockwise after the initial impact, contacting it's left rear with the front of V3 which was stopped waiting to turn at the exit of the private drive.

V1 was making a left hand turn at a T intersection, intending to head southbound on the intersecting roadway. V2 was traveling northbound in the #2 lane at the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2 in the intersection.
V1 was traveling north on 2 way undivided roadway attempting a left hand turn to continue west. V2 was traveling behind V1. V1's front end contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway, making a left hand turn to continue south.  V1 departed the right side of the road during the turn and contacted a concrete culvert with its undercarriage.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling west in lane one of a four lane undivided roadway. V2 and V3 began to decelerate for traffic ahead. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. The impact to the back of V2 pushed it forward, and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3. All vehicles came to a final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 departed the road to the left and impacted a wood utility pole, located at the top of a grass ditch, with the front plane. After impact with the pole, V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the ditch.

V1 was traveling westbound on a six lane major highway in lane six. V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 impacted a concrete barrier.  V1 then impacted the concrete barrier with it's left side in a sideswipe manner.
V1 was traveling northbound toward an intersection and V2 was going east toward the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling west, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection, in lane 2. At the intersection, V1 turned left. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.
Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling east on a divided 4 lane roadway with 2 eastbound lanes, when deer entered the roadway. The front of Vehicle 1 collided with the back of Vehicle 2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane one of a divided roadway with two westbound lanes. Vehicle #2 was traveling behind V1. V1's front struck the back of V2. V2 departed the roadway on the right side and rolled four quarter turns on the left side.

Vehicle1 was traveling south on a two lane two way roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the intersecting two lane two way roadway. Vehicle 1 struck the right side plane of Vehicle 2 with its frontal plane.  Vehicle 2 began to rotate clockwise, departing the roadway to the left,  striking a stop sign, located on the southwest shoulder of the intersection, with its left side plane. Vehicle 1 came to rest south of the intersection headed south on the west side of the roadway.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway. Vehicle 1 struck a cow with its frontal plane and came to rest on the south side of the roadway.

V1 was exiting a private business westbound, attempting to make a left turn to continue  south. V2 was traveling in the number two lane on the intersecting  5 lane non-divided road. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound and V2 was traveling southbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V3 was parked off the roadway and to the west of the roadway. The right side of V1 contacted the front end of V2. V2 came to rest on the roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left, striking multiple objects before overturning on top of V3.
V1 was traveling southwest on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side, its front plane contacting a tree.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound in lane one on a two lane roadway. V1 attempted to overtake V2 on the right shoulder. V2, which was towing a trailer, attempted to turn right into a driveway. The front of V1 struck the right side of V2. After the collision with V2, V1 rolled right along its longitudinal axis. As V1 traveled on its right side rotating counter clockwise, the top of V1 struck an 8 cm iron fence post. V1 continued rotating clockwise and the top of V1 struck a bush. V1 came to rest facing northeast on its right side on the shoulder and partially in lane one.

V1 traveling southeast exiting a parking lot. V2 was traveling southwest in lane 3 on a five lane two-way center turn lane divided roadway. V1 attempted to exit the parking lot and travel across all lanes of traffic to continue into a parking lot on the opposite side of the roadway. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane 1 of a 2 lane road, negotiating a curve to its left. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front impacted a fiberglass mile marker. The vehicle continued traveling off the roadway and into a ditch. The vehicle rolled 1/4 turn to the right and the front  of V1 contacted the ditch embankment.  V1 right side then contacted the ditch embankment.  V1 came to rest on its wheels facing north in the ditch.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a divided roadway with three eastbound lanes, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue north.  Vehicle 2 was westbound on the same roadway. V3 was stopped facing south in a driveway. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 continued west and began to rotate clockwise, entering the driveway where the front of V2 contacted the front of V3.
