V1 continued north, traveling into an adjacent driving, departing the roadway to the left side striking the curb.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a one lane split exit roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side, its front plane contacting a ditch on the roadside. V1 crossed through the adjacent exit lane and the right side of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier.

Vehicle 1 was backing up westbound into an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound in the first of two lanes approaching that intersection. Within the intersection the back of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was passing through an intersection traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right side of the road and the front of V1 contacted a fire hydrant. V1 then impacted it's right side on the remaining part of the fire hydrant sticking out of the ground and came to final rest in the road.
V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road when it departed the right side of the road, down a slight embankment, and impacted a tree  with it's front plane.

V1 was traveling northbound on a four lane, two way roadway. V2 was traveling southbound on the same roadway.  V1 began to yaw on the icy roadway and departed its lane to the left.  The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was eastbound in lane one of a three lane road entering a 4-way intersection. V2 was in lane one of a  five lane road southbound entering the same intersection. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.
Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were westbound on a three lane, two-way roadway.   Vehicle #1's front end collided with Vehicle #2's back end.

V2 was traveling east in the number 2 lane of a four lane roadway composed of an eastbound travel lane, an eastbound acceleration lane, a westbound travel and a westbound dedicated left turn lane. V1 was traveling on the same roadway behind V2. The front of V1 collided with the rear of V2.

V1 was approaching an intersection while traveling westbound in lane three of a five lane two way roadway divided by a median.  V2 was approaching the same intersection traveling eastbound in lane three of a 6 lane two way roadway divided by a median. V1 entered the intersection to travel southbound and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection.  V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a three lane two way undivided roadway in lane one approaching a four way intersection. V1 departed the northeast intersection apex and impacted with the curb. V1 continued northeast across a grassy area into a parking lot. The front of V1 contacted a cement parking block and came to final rest on top of the cement parking block.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane two of a divided roadway with two northbound lanes. V1 departed its lane to the right, then departed the roadway to the right and traveled up an embankment. The front right wheel of V1 contacted an unknown object causing damage before it rolled over four quarter turns to the left.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a five lane roadway, attempting to make a left hand turn into a parking lot.  Vehicle #2 was traveling east on the same roadway. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling NE in lane 1 of a divided, roadway (two NE lanes and two SW lanes). V1 began to change lanes to the left, then continue to depart the road to the left and entered the median. The front plane contacted a rocky embankment (Event 1). The LF, LR and RF wheels also contacted the embankment (Events 2-4). Vehicle #2 was traveling SW when it was impacted by debris that was kicked up by Vehicle #1 (Event 5).

V2 was traveling south in the second lane of a three lane divided roadway approaching an exit ramp. V1 was traveling south in the first lane of a three lane divided roadway approaching the same ramp. V1 departed the first lane into the second lane in an attempt to pass V2 as its lane became a exit only lane. The front of V1 contacted V2 on the right side (Event 1). V1 and V2 make a left departure from the second and third lanes. The front of V2 contacted the guardrail face (Event 2). The front of V1 contacted the guardrail face rotating counterclockwise causing continuous damage along the right side and back (Event 3). V1 then crossed all three lanes to the right, where it came to final rest facing east in the first lane. V2 rotated counterclockwise and the back contacted the guardrail face (Event 4). V2 continued to rotate and came to final rest facing east with the front contacting the guardrail (Event 5). V1 occupant one was ejected fro the vehicle during its rotation from the guardrail to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound in the second lane of a two lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the left side. The left side plane of V1 then impacted a tree and continued down an embankment where it came to final rest.
V1 departed a private lot on the east road side and entered a four lane, two way roadway and headed southbound.  V1 departed the west roadside and the front of V1 contacted an embankment.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway, entering a sing controlled intersection.. V2 was traveling south on the intersecting two lane, two way roadway entering the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. A second impact occurred as the front of V1 then contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was leaving a parked position heading southbound on a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction.  V2 was traveling southbound in the right lane of the same roadway.  On this roadway, the frontal plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the right lane on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel and a two way turning lane in each direction. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. At the above intersection, as V2 was making a left turn to go northbound, the frontal plane of V2 made impact with the right plane of V1. After the impact, V1 started to yaw moving clockwise and departed the roadway on the right side. The left plane/wheel made impact with the curb as V1 was continuing departing the roadway. The left plane of V1 then made impact with a Tree and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling east on an unmarked two lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was southbound in lane one on a four lane undivided roadway.  V1 entered into the intersection to make a left turn from a stop sign. V2 entered into the same intersection heading straight. The front of V2 impacted with the left of V1 (event 1).  V1 rotated counter clockwise and left reconnected with the front of V2 (event 2).  V2 departed the roadway to the right where its right collided with a utility pole (event 3) where it came to final rest. V1 came to final rest facing northbound in the northbound lanes.
V1 was westbound negotiating a right curve when it departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a utility pole. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane unmarked roadway, negotiating a right hand curve, when it departed its lane and the roadway on the left. V1's left front and left rear wheels/tires contacted the curb.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west.  Vehicle #2 was traveling east on the same roadway.  V1 began to turn left at an intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2 again.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non divided roadway V2 was traveling north bound on the intersecting two lane non divided roadway.  V1's frontal plane impacted V2's left plane. V2 rotated clockwise, where V2's left side impacted V1's right side before both vehicles came to final rest.

V1 was northbound on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve. V1 departed the right side (east) of the roadway traveling into a ditch impacting a culvert with the frontal plane. Upon impact V1 became airborne over a driveway. The front of V1 contacted and traveled through tree limbs before impacting a tree with the front plane. V1 came to final rest in the ditch facing north.

V1 and V2 were northbound on a two lane road divided by a median. V1 attempted to make a left hand U-turn. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 causing damage. V1 and V2 continued to the left (east) where the right side of V2 impacted the left side of V1 two more times. Both vehicles came to final rest in the opposite travel lane facing east.

V1 was attempting to make a left hand turn from the #3 lane to head westbound on the roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in the #1 lane at the same intersection. V1's right side and V2's front side made contact with each other in the intersection. The vehicles then rotated and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was northbound in lane one on a three lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was eastbound in lane one on the five lane, two way undivided intersecting roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection traveling straight and the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was going southbound entering an off ramp and ran off roadway left striking a guard rail end with the frontal plane. V1 returned to the roadway after this impact and crossed over two lanes entering onto the right shoulder of the roadway. V1 re-entered the travel lanes and V1 front contacted V2 right.  V1 then entered into a counterclockwise yaw and contacted the jersey barrier with the right rear corner.
V1 was north bound on a two lane non divided roadway when V1 left the roadway to the right and impacted three trees with its frontal plane.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway passing through an intersection. V2  was traveling north on the two lane two way intersecting roadway through the intersection. The front plane of V2 contacted the right rear plane of V1 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a 2 way non divided roadway when the front plane of the vehicle impacted a fallen tree in the roadway. V1 continued under the tree, emerging beyond it with damage to the front and top planes.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south bound on a two lane roadway. V1 departed the lane on the left side and then departed the roadway on the left side. V1 contacted a sign with the front bumper of the vehicle. V1 then rolled to it's left side four quarter turns.
V1 was traveling south in lane one of a three lane divided roadway.  A deer entered the road and made contact with the front end of V1.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a 2 way undivided roadway approaching a 4-way intersection.  V2 was traveling west in lane 1 of a 2-way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection.  The front end of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection.  The impact caused V1 and V2 to depart the roadway at the northwest apex of the intersection where V2 came to a final rest and V1 made contact with its right side to a sign post.

Vehicle 1 was accelerating from a stopped position, heading east, through a 4 leg intersection. Vehicle 2 was accelerating from a stopped position, heading north through the 4 leg intersection. The frontal plane of vehicle 2 struck the right side plane of vehicle 1 causing damage to both. Vehicle 1 came to rest in the eastbound lane, headed east, and east of the intersection. Vehicle 2 came to rest at the point of impact headed north.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway.  V1 departed the left (north) road edge. The front of V1 contacted a sign.  V1 came to final rest off of the roadway in an embankment.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, two-lane road. The road descended slightly and curved to the left. V1 departed the right side of the road, climbing an embankment. V1 then rolled left side leading four-quarter turns and landed on its wheels.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane roadway preparing to turn left onto southbound lanes at an intersection.  V2 was northbound on the two lane intersecting roadway. V2 entered an intersection turning left. The front of V2 impacted with the left rear tire of V1.  V1 came to final rest in the southbound lanes against the curb. V2 came to final rest in the northbound lanes against the curb.
V1 and V2 were traveling south approaching an intersection with V2 ahead of V1. V2 slowed and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway ahead of V1. V1 was traveling in the westbound lane overtaking two vehicles on the right. V2 was making a left hand turn into a driveway crossing the path of V1. The front plane of V1 contacted V2 on the left plane causing V1 to come to final rest in a driveway off of the roadway, while V2 came to final rest on the eastbound shoulder.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a four lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest on the intersecting roadway and entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left front side of V2.

V1 was headed east in the first lane of a three-lane divided roadway. V2 was headed east in the first lane of a three-lane divided roadway ahead of V1. A non-contact vehicle was traveling in between V1 & V2 in the first lane of a three-lane undivided roadway. V2 stopped in the road and the non-contact vehicle successfully avoided a collision with V2 by departing the lane to the left.  V1's frontal plane contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the second lane of a two lane roadway. V2 was attempting to make a left turn to head northbound. The frontal plane of V2 impacted the right side plane of V1 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a one way, two lane road. V2 was parked in a private driveway with the back end of its flatbed in the roadway. V1's front contacted the rear of V2. V1 then rotated clockwise across the roadway, departing the roadway to the left and then coming back onto roadway backwards and departing the roadway to the right. V1 struck a curb with its left side before coming to final rest facing west.

V1 was traveling north approaching an intersection on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling east in lane one of a three lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's right plane in the intersection as both vehicles proceeded straight. As the vehicles began to rotate the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V2 then departed the northeast intersection apex and the front plane of V2 contacted a pole.
Vehicle 1 was eastbound in the second of four lanes. Vehicle 2 was eastbound in the first of four lanes. The driver of V1 changed lanes to the right. The back of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane three on a three lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in lane two on the three lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted a left turn in the intersection. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection. Subsequently, debris impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  V2, V3 and V4 were traveling westbound on the same roadway stopped ahead of V1.  V5 was traveling eastbound on the same roadway.  The right side of V1 contacted the back of V2.  The front of V2 then contacted the back of V3.  The front of V3 then contacted the back of V4.  The left side of V1 then contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane 1 of a two-way not physically divided roadway with bicycle lanes on both east and west edges of the roadway prior to the shoulder. V2 was legally parked facing northbound on the right shoulder. V1 departed the roadway on the right and crossed the bicycle lane into the shoulder. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 continued traveling northbound and re-entered the roadway where the front left tire impacted the center median curb divider. V1 came to rest at the curb impact

Vehicle #1 was traveling NE. V1 departed the road to the right, and its front plane contacted a mile marker. V1 over-corrected to the left, rotating counter-clockwise. V1 re-entered the road and departed it to the left. V1 tripped over four quarter turns to the right.

Vehicles 1, 2,and 3 were all northbound in lane three of a three-lane, one-way road.  Vehicles 1 and 2 were stopped ahead of V3. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Subsequently, the front of V2 impacted the back of V3.

V1 was traveling towards an intersection in the northbound left turn (#3) lane and attempted a left turn towards a westbound interstate ramp. V2 was traveling southbound in the #1 lane approaching the same intersection. V2's front end made contact with V1's right front corner.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on an undivided 2 lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on an intersecting, undivided 2 lane roadway. When both vehicles entered into the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 spun 180 degrees and came to rest in the northwest corner of the intersection. Vehicle 2 continued in a northerly direction turning in a counter clockwise rotation. Vehicle 2 traveled through the ditch on the west side of the roadway where the driver's side of the vehicle scraped the embankment (POI #2), traveled through the ditch and over a pasture fence (POI #3), into the pasture and into an irrigation ditch where it laid over on it's left side onto a small sapling (POI #4) and the ground (POI #5) at final rest. Both vehicles were towed from the scene.

V1, V2, V3, V4, V5, and V6 were all traveling northeast on a 6 lane interstate in the number 5 lane. V2, V3, V4, V5, and V6 were all stopped due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The force of the impact pushed the front of V2 into the rear of V3. The force of this impact pushed the front of V3 into the rear of V4. The force of this impact pushed the front of V4 into the rear of V5. The force of this impact pushed the front of V5 into the rear of V6. After the successive impacts all vehicles came to final rest in the number 5 lane facing northeast.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane two way undivided roadway.  V1 traveled across the eastbound travel lane and departed the north road edge. V1 went down an embankment and the undercarriage of V1 contacted a ditch.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way roadway with one lane of travel and a two way turning lane in each direction. V2 was traveling in the same direction in front of V1. As V2 was stopped in traffic, the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane 2 of a one-way roadway with four lanes of travel.  V2 was traveling in lane 1 of the same roadway attempting to change lanes.  On this roadway, the left side of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway with traffic in opposite directions attempting to turn left at an intersection of on and off ramps of a limited access roadway. V2 was traveling west through the same intersection. As V1 began making the left turn onto the on ramp, the front of V1 collided with the front of V2.

V3 was stopped, facing a northerly direction in lane 1 of the Interstate.  V2 was traveling north on the Interstate in lane 1, and was approaching V3.  V1 was traveling north on the Interstate in lane 2, and was to the left and rear of V2.  The driver of V2 steered V2 to the left and into lane 2 in an attempt to avoid V3.  The driver of V1 steered V1 to the left in an attempt to avoid V2.  The front end of V1 came into contact with the back end of V2 (Event 1).  The front end of V2 came into contact with the back end of V3 (Event 2).  The front end of V1 then came into contact with the concrete traffic barrier in the median (Event 3).  The front end and right side of V3 then came into contact with the concrete traffic barrier along the right edge of the road (Events 4, 5 and 6), and V3 rotated clockwise counter-clockwise.  During V3's rotation, its left side came into contact with V2 (Event 7).

V1 was traveling from east attempted to turn and travel north through at an intersection. V2 was traveling west through the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was southbound traveling behind V2. V2 was stopped in the middle of the road waiting to turn left. V1 attempted to pass V2 to the left and as V2 began the left turn the left side of V2 contacted the right side of V1.
V1 was northbound in lane one of a 4 lane divided highway when the vehicle was struck by falling rocks.
V1 and V2 were traveling west in lane three of a seven lane undivided roadway. V1 was behind V2. V2 began to move forward then stopped. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V2 was traveling north, attempting to make a right turn into a business. V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way roadway behind V2. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2 (Event 1). V2 departed the right side of the road where the left front tire/rim  contacted the curb (Event 2) before initiating a rollover sequence (Event 3). The right-quarter-panel of V2 impacted a tree in a non-horizontal impact (Event 4), before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling eastbound approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic signal; V2 was traveling northbound attempting to cross through the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the middle of the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a 2 lane non divided roadway when it crossed the right lane line and its front plane contacted a legally street parked V2 on its left side plane. V1 then continued to travel east and departed the roadway, contacting a utility pole with its front plane.

V1 was attempting to make a right hand turn from a private driveway on a two lane non divided roadway. V2 was north bound on the roadway. V1 right plane impacted V2's frontal plane. V1's right plane then impacted V2's left plane.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a three lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane three of a three lane service road approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound on a four lane roadway in the number 2 lane.  V2 was traveling northbound on the same roadway. V1 departed two travel lanes to the left. The front of V1 impacted with the left of V2.  V1 came to final rest in the center of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a 3 lane divided highway in the number 3 lane when the front of V1 struck a cow laying in the road. V1 came to rest in the number 2 lane. After V1 stabilized it was contacted in the rear and pushed into a bridge section. The rear and right side damage are not related to this crash.

V2 was traveling southwest in the first lane on a two way non-physically divided roadway. V1 was traveling southeast in the first lane on a two way non-physically divided roadway. V1 and V2 traveled into intersection. The front of V2 impacted with the left side of V1, continuing contact down the right side of V2 and the left side of V1. V2 then rotated slightly counter clockwise and came to final rest facing south. V1 came to final rest facing south in the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane non physically divided roadway when it lost control due to icy road conditions.  V1 started to fishtail and began to rotate counter clockwise sliding into the southbound lane.  V2, which was traveling South, attempted to avoid collision by moving over to the shoulder.  The right side of V1 made contact with the front of V2.  V2 continued south striking a guardrail face.

V1 was heading westbound and V2 was traveling eastbound on the same roadway. V1 lost control and began to rotate counterclockwise. V1 crossed over center line and V2's front contacted V1's right side. V1 then rolled over top of V2 and came to rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 2 was traveling east bound in the second of four lanes on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 1 was stopped at a stop sign facing south. V1 attempted to turn right heading west bound, crossed two lanes of traffic and entered the eastbound travel lanes. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 3 lane road in the number 1 lane entering an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a 3 lane road in the number 3 lane. V2 was making a left hand turn through the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 then rotated counter clockwise and came to final rest in the northbound number 1 lane facing south and V2 came to rest facing northbound on the northeast corner of the intersection on the sidewalk.

Both Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling northbound on a one way 2 lane roadway in the #2 lane. Vehicle 2 stopped for traffic ahead. Vehicle 1 attempted to avoid contact by braking and steering to the right. Vehicle 1's front end and Vehicle 2's rear made contact with each other.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the third lane of a seven lane, two way roadway.  V2 and V3 were stopped in the third eastbound lane ahead of V1.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  The front of V2 then contacted the back of V3.

Vehicles #2 was stopped facing south at an intersection. Vehicle #1 was traveling south in the same lane. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. After impact, V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise and departed the road into the center median where the rear of V1 contacted a sign post.
V1 was northbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 impacted a deer with the frontal plane causing damage.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided residential roadway. V1 departed the road to the right and the front plane contacted a fence.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane two of a four lane divided highway. V1 traveled southwest across the remaining travel lanes and departed the roadway on the left. The front of V1 then contacted a concrete traffic barrier.
V1 was stopped at a four-way intersection on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling in the same direction and braking due to stopped traffic. The front of V2 contacted the rear of V1.

Vehicle 1 was going westbound approaching an intersection. Vehicle 1 encountered icy conditions as it attempted to stop. Due to this, V1 entered into the intersection while attempting to brake and was struck on its left side plane by Vehicle 2 frontal plane.

V1 was traveling westbound on a four-lane roadway divided by a concrete barrier, approaching an intersection. V2 was approaching the same four-way intersection intending to pass through heading southbound. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. After initial impact V1 continued off the roadway to the left and its wheels contacted the sloped face of the concrete barrier. The impact with the concrete barrier caused V1 to overturn four-quarter turns across the roadway before coming to final rest on its wheels. During the rollover maneuver, V1 was airborne where and the left side of V1 a traffic light.  After the initial impact, V2 rotated clockwise and its left side contacted the center concrete barrier.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way roadway when the vehicle departed the right side of the road and struck an embankment.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane divided road in lane 2 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a undivided two lane road approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V2 began to rotate clockwise and the right side of V2 impacted the left side of V1 as the vehicles began to rotate. V1 departed the roadway to the northwest and the front of V1 impacted a stop sign.

V1 was traveling in lane one on a two way undivided roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling in the westbound lane of a two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered intersection proceeding in straight paths. The front of V2 contacted the right of V1. V1 came to final rest facing north in southbound lane. V2 came to final rest facing west in original lane.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane 2 of a four lane divided roadway.. V1 departed the roadway on the left side and contacted a light pole in the median.

V1 was traveling in a southerly direction in the #4 left turn lane attempting to make a left hand turn at an intersection. V2 was traveling northerly direction in the #3 lane approaching the same intersection. V1's right side and V2's front end made contact with each other. V1 continued through the intersection after the initial contact then departed the roadway in the intersection on the southeast corner. V1 contacted a traffic signal support pole on the southeast corner of the intersection, knocking the pole down, before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling east in lane 4 on a six-lane physically divided roadway. V2 and V3 were stopped in the same lane at the intersection when the front of V1 contacted the back of V2 and the front of V2 contacted the back of V3.
V1 was eastbound on a three lane, two way road. V2 was legally parked along the south curb facing east. The front of V1 struck the rear of V2. V1 then rolled, coming to rest on its wheels.

As V1 was traveling east in lane 2 on a three-lane roadway which intersects a two-lane roadway, its front end contacted the back end of V2, which was stopped in lane 2 (for the STOP sign), facing an easterly direction, at the entrance to the intersection.

V2 was traveling west negotiating a left curve on a two lane undivided roadway with traffic in opposite directions. V1 was traveling east on the same roadway. As V1 initiated a left turn into an intersecting northbound street the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection and began to turn left. The front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1.
